title: spoon bread
directions: Stir soup until smooth and gradually blend in milk.
Add cornmeal and cook until thickened, stirring all the while.
Add butter and remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; stir into mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold into mixture.
Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve with butter and/or syrup.

title: venison burgers
directions: Saute
onions,	parsley
and garlic in butter.	Combine onion mixture with meat and seasoning.
Form into patties and grill to desired doneness.

title: mama's butter roll
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Combine first four ingredients. Roll dough, with rolling pin, between 2 sheets of waxed paper until thick like pie crust (about 10 X 12 inches).
Cover with 1/4 inch pats of margarine.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar.
Sprinkle vanilla over sugar.
Roll and seal dough together.
Cut 1 inch slices of roll.
Place in a 9 X 9 baking dish that has been sprayed with PAM. Pour 1 1/2 cups milk or cream (for richer flavor) over top of rolls.
Bake at 350 until lightly brown.

title: crazy cake(no egg cake)
directions: Mix first 5 dry ingredients.
Add remainder.
Mix and put into 13 x 9 cake pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
This is a very dense cake and is wonderful with one of the chocolate frosting recipes.
It is really good the next day after it sits.

title: zucchini cake
directions: In large bowl, sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Blend in sugar.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla; beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Add zucchini, raisins, nuts and coconut and blend.
Spoon batter into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: 9 pound fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add 3 1/2 cups of the flour and the juice.
Add the other cup of flour to the fruits to coat them; fold in egg whites.
Line pan with waxed paper.
Grease so the paper will stick to pan.
Cover the cake and pan with foil to keep out the water drops from the steam.
Place 2 inches water in pressure canner; leave the cockpit open until the steam comes out and steam for 30 minutes.
Then close cockpit and cook 35 minutes at 5 pounds pressure, then raise to 10 pounds pressure and cook 40 minutes.
When cooking time is over, let cake stay in canner 30 minutes before removing lid.
Then cool and wrap.
You can bake this a long time before Christmas.
It will keep and will be better the older it is.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make a golden roux of oil and flour.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook slowly until clear.
Add tomato sauce and cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp, salt and peppers.
Add water, if necessary.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
When ready to serve, stir in parsley.
Serve on rice.

title: apple pie cake
directions: In three quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat - remove from heat.
Blend in sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix until blended.
Turn into greased and floured 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes (until top springs back). Serve warm or cold.
Great with Cool Whip!

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Mix in all remaining ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mom's sloppy joes
directions: Cook celery and onion in small amount of water until tender. Set aside.
Brown hamburger.
Add cooked onions and celery; stir. Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Put in large casserole and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Gets better each time you warm it up.

title: dad's italian meatballs
directions: Combine all the ingredients until well blended and fry in 10 or 12-inch skillet to which 1 tablespoon of cooking oil has been added, adding more as needed while frying.
Makes approximately 40 to 45 large meatballs.
Can be eaten as is or combined with spaghetti sauce for pasta.
Good luck and enjoy!

title: turkey gumbo soup
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Add vegetables, seasonings, rice and turkey.
Cover and cook slowly 15 minutes until vegetables and rice are tender.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: four onion soup
directions: Slice onions 1/4-inch thick. In a 3-quart saucepan over medium-low heat, saute onions and garlic in butter for 15 minutes or until tender and golden, stirring occasionally. Add broth, consomme, Worcestershire sauce and nutmeg. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon Swiss cheese in bottom of 6 ovenproof 8-ounce bowls.
Ladle hot soup into bowls. Top each with a slice of bread. Sprinkle with remaining Swiss and Parmesan cheese, if desired; broil until cheese melts. Serve immediately.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Put all ingredients, except cabbage wedges, in 4-quart crock-pot in order listed. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (high 5 to 6 hours).
Add cabbage wedges to liquid, pushing down to moisten.
Turn to high and cook an additional 2 to 3 hours.

title: unbaked butterscotch bars
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and butter.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Stir in marshmallows and cracker crumbs.
Spread in pan.
Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Add vanilla.
Spread over crumb mixture. Refrigerate.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Layer ground beef in bottom of pan; layer potatoes on top of meat, then onions.
Mix together soups and water.
Stir together and pour over the meat, potatoes and onions.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not salt.

title: watermelon punch
directions: Cut an oblong hole in top of watermelon; scoop out watermelon meat.
Remove seeds; mash half the watermelon meat.
Mix watermelon juice, lemon juice, ginger ale, and crushed ice; pour into watermelon rind which is used for punch bowl.
Chill remaining watermelon meat for second servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion (drain).
Add cheese, soup and enchilada sauce, mixing well.
Place tortilla shells in 8-inch glass baking dish.
Pour hamburger mixture over shells.
Microwave on High until cheese is melted.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix together in a casserole.
Bake for 3 hours or until tender at 325°.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: jordyn's mom's banana bread
directions: Mix bananas, sugar, eggs and oleo.
Add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in prepared loaf pan.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to the package directions.
Drain.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Combine with soup.
Mix in some cheese.
Put cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: real pizza(low-fat, vegetarian)
directions: Once dough has risen for the second time, punch down and knead lightly.
Pat and stretch dough to cover bottom and about 1 1/2 inches up sides of a greased, heavy 10-inch cast-iron frying pan or deep dish pizza pan or a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Dough will shrink back at first but keep working it.
Cover with tomato sauce, Mozzarella and the vegetables.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Bake on bottom rack for 10 minutes or until crust is browned.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix first
4 ingredients together well.
Add corn bread mix. Pour in a greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: frozen cukes
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice thin.
Put in salted, cold water. Boil water, sugar, vinegar and spice.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand until cool.
Put in small Baggies.
Put in freezer.
Ready to use right away.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat
eggs
lightly.
Add
sugar
and salt; blend well. Add vanilla
and
milk.
Flour
pie plate.
Pour into pastry-lined plate and sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 10 to
15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until custard is firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lemon brownies
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and press in 9 x 13-inch pan, then mix the next 4 ingredients.
Pour over the first three and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: very easy carrot cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and baby food carrots.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl; add milk, oil and corn.
Stir until well mixed.
Fold in eggs (well beaten). Cook on griddle.
Turn, browning both sides.

title: turkey with mushroom-wine sauce
directions: Cut turkey into eight 1/4-inch slices; set aside.
Lightly brown mushrooms in butter in a large skillet.
Combine cornstarch, bouillon and garlic powder in small bowl; gradually stir in water and sherry. Add to skillet and cook on medium, stirring until mixture thickens and begins to boil.
Add turkey. Cover and simmer 10 minutes more. Serve turkey with sauce.
Makes 4 servings containing 219 calories per serving.

title: baked ham steak
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Combine sugar and allspice.
Spoon mixture evenly over top of ham all around sides.
Place ham in shallow baking dish.
Pour apricot nectar around ham.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour, basting occasionally with pan liquid.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Thaw lemonade. Mix with condensed milk.
Blend in lite Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Can be frozen.
Best served when partially frozen.
Delicious for summer dessert.

title: ma ma cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.

title: good luck pie crust
directions: With
a
fork, mix together flour, shortening, sugar and water.
In
a
separate
dish,
beat
remaining
ingredients. Combine the 2 mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are
moistened.
Then
with hands mold dough into a ball. Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling it into desired shape or it can be frozen.
Yield: 2 (9-inch) double crust pies or 3 (9-inch) shells.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour; stir in buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add egg whites (beaten) and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except pecans.
Top with pecans. Can be heated at 325° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers or pumpernickel bread.

title: chocolate drink mix
directions: In large mixing bowl combine dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and put in airtight containers.

title: apple bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Peel, core & slice apples; cut apples in half crosswise. Unroll dough, separate at perforations. Place 4 apple slices at the wide end of dough & roll up. Arrange in baking dish. Pour juice into bottom of baking dish, but not over bundles. Brush melted butter over bundles. Mix sugar & cinnamon; sprinkle over bundles. Bake 25-30 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 16 servings.

title: fire dept. marinated steak
directions: Using a fork, poke steak many times on both sides.
Place steak in closeable marinating dish.

title: chic salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Melt Jell-O with water.
Fold in other ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish and chill until firm.

title: beer balls
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients and make into small balls.
Put onto cookie sheet and brown under broiler.
Take out with slotted spoon so grease doesn't get into sauce.
Place browned meatballs into sauce with first 5 ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Good for appetizers for parties.

title: crunchies(cookies)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in oats, cornflakes, coconut and pecans.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: peach and cream dessert
directions: Stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and butter; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 inch pan (I use a deep pie dish).
Drain peaches, reserving 1/3 c. of liquid.
Chop peaches and sprinkle on top of batter.
Beat together softened cream cheese, sugar and 1/3 c. peach liquid.
Pour on top of peaches.
Combine 1 Tbsp. sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool before serving.

title: cranberry salad(serves 9)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Combine Jell-O and sugar. Add water to juice to make 2 cups. Heat and add to Jell-O mixture. Add lemon juice. Chill until partially set. Grind together cranberries, orange and nuts and add to Jell-O mix. Stir in pineapple. Place in 8 x 8 dish. Refrigerate.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cut margarine and Velveeta cheese in small lumps in large saucepan.
Add water and salt.
Bring to a boil and add grits. Turn off stove; stir until smooth.
Then add beaten eggs.
Pour into large, greased baking dish and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until top starts browning.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onions and celery until tender (not brown), then add to soup mixture.
Also add light cream, salt and pepper.
Garnish with parsley.

title: garden salad
directions: Pour dressing over vegetables and let sit for a few hours in fridge.
Can add other vegetables, if desired (green or red peppers, mushrooms, onions, etc.).

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the shortening or margarine and sugar. Add the egg and molasses and mix well. Combine the flour, ground ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Add about 1/4 dry mixture to the creamed mixture at a time and mix well after each addition.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place well apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Tops will crack.
Makes 4 or 5 dozen cookies.

title: holiday scallop
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions separately.
Peel cooked potatoes. Mix sour cream and cottage cheese together.
Mix salt, pepper and thyme.
Layer sliced potatoes, onions and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with mixed spices.
Top with sour cream/cottage cheese mixture. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.

title: hollywood cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter together and pat in bottom of spring-form pan.
Have the cream cheese and eggs at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and 3/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in crust and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until firm.
Take cake out of oven and cool for 10 minutes.
Mix well the sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla; pour cream mixture on cake.
Turn up oven to 450°.
Put back in oven for 10 minutes or it sets well.
Remove from form pan when cool.

title: orange chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken. Place in 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole. Pour orange soda and soy sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dressing for fresh fruits
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well and refrigerate.
To serve, spoon over any kind or assortment of fresh fruit (bananas, strawberries, honeydew, cantaloupe, apples, grapes, pineapple, blueberries, etc.).
Very good.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Beat all ingredients and fold in chocolate chips.
Grease a Teflon iron Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 45 minutes and invert.
Sprinkle sifted powdered sugar on top.

title: chocolate chess squares
directions: Combine flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture into bottom of foil-lined 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: french toast
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Dip one slice bread into mixture and fry until golden brown, about 2 minutes each side.
Remove from skillet; add butter and syrup and serve.

title: applesauce
directions: Cook ingredients until tender.
Mash the apples with a potato masher or electric mixer, adding more sugar if desired.
Serve cold.

title: red, white, blue fruit platter
directions: Place pineapple, blueberries and strawberries in separate bowls.
Mix ginger ale and marmalade in small bowl.
Add to fruit, dividing evenly.
Toss gently.
Chill 2 hours.

title: loin of pork in sherry
directions: Have your butcher cut through the bones in back to ease separating chops.
Have him trim all visible fat (he won't!).
Trim away all fat possible.
Rub the loin with salt, pepper and garlic. Season for two hours at room temperature if you will.
Heat oil in large pan and brown pork on all sides.
Pour off fat and add sherry.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring undiluted soup to boil.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth and melted.
Add gelatin and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and put into mold.
Remove a half-hour before serving. Serve on crackers.
Serves 24.

title: hadas' pretzels
directions: Measure warm water into large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle on yeast. Stir until looks soft.
Add salt, sugar and flour.
Mix and knead.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook on low heat for 2 hours.
Add potatoes last 45 minutes. Add macaroni as served.

title: sauce piquant
directions: I use round steak for meat.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat ingredients and blend in chopped nuts (if desired). Serve with sliced apples which have been dipped in orange juice.

title: quick creamed chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in shallow baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix above ingredients and put in 8 large buns. Wrap in foil. Bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes or 350° oven for 10-15 minutes. These may be frozen and heated as needed.

title: dutch baby apple pancakes
directions: Lightly beat flour, milk, egg, juice and salt.
Melt butter in 9-inch ovenproof skillet.
Pour mixture into pan and arrange apples over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden and puffy.
Sprinkle with combined sugar and cinnamon.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in four (1-pound) coffee cans.

title: aunt ruth's society punch
directions: Mix sugar and 4 cups water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Chill, then add drained pineapple syrup, juice from oranges and 4 cups ice water. Add sliced oranges.
Add crushed or grated pineapple from which syrup has been drained.
Add maraschino cherries.
Pour over block of ice in a punch bowl. This will serve 25 persons.

title: grandma klauser's apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand.
Sift dry ingredients; mix with apple mixture.
Add egg, oil, vanilla and nuts; mix well. Pour package of butterscotch morsels over top.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: milky way cake(a favorite at all events!)
directions: Grind pecans thoroughly in small batches in a chopper machine or blender.
Cream butter by leaving at room temperature 1 hour or microwave on "2" for 1 minute.

title: magic pie
directions: Roll gingersnaps to fine crumbs.
Combine butter and press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Pour pudding mix into bowl.
Add milk; beat 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until well blended.
Turn into crust.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry squares
directions: Mix flour, walnuts, brown sugar and butter until crumbly. Place in a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Whip egg whites, sugar, strawberries and lemon juice for 10 minutes.
Fold whipped cream into strawberry mixture.
Place 1/2 of crumble mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan, cover with strawberry mix, then crumble rest of mixture on top.
Cover and freeze for 6 hours.

title: hot cider and spice
directions: Fill crock-pot with cider. Sprinkle pumpkin spice. Decrease spice accordingly for a lesser quantity. Heat for one hour after cider is hot. May be kept hot on low setting for several hours.

title: cioppino (seafood stew)
directions: Saute onion and garlic over moderate heat in olive oil until soft but not browned. Add parsley, tomatoes, tomato sauce, wine, Clamato juice, vinegar and herbs. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes. (Basic sauce can be made ahead, cooled, covered and refrigerated. Heat sauce before adding to seafood.)

title: pizza snacks
directions: Divide frozen bread dough in half.
Spread in greased 10 x 10-inch or 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with 1 or 2 layers sliced pepperoni, shredded cheese and beaten eggs.
Top with other half of bread dough; brush top with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden and eggs are cooked.

title: antipasto platter
directions: Cover a large platter with lettuce leaves.
Drain can of white beans and pile in center of platter.
Break tuna into chunks and place on beans.
Fill the rest of the platter with black olives, diagonally cut carrot and celery pieces, chunks of Provolone cheese, salami slices and cherry tomatoes.
Pour dressing over all.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: raisin spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 6 1/2-inch square baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium saucepan, combine raisins, margarine,
sugar	and 1/2 cup of water.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and set aside to cool.
Stir in beaten egg.
In a
medium bowl, stir together remaining ingredients. Add
to raisin
mixture,
stirring just until combined.
Pour batter
into prepared dish.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 15 minutes.
Healthy.	Serves 4.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter in shallow pan over low heat.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Chex and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in a 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes. Spread out on an absorbent paper towel to cool.

title: fried corn
directions: Shuck corn.
Wash and remove silk.
After cutting the kernels in half with a sharp knife, cut kernels with the blunt side of the knife.

title: cocoa cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with sugar and butter.
Press mixture onto bottom and halfway up side of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: patty's potatoes
directions: Cube and cook potatoes like you would for mashed potatoes. Drain and mash with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: no-cook freezer jam
directions: Measure sugar, then thoroughly stir in fruit.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix 3/4 cup water and Sure-Jell fruit pectin in small saucepan.
Bring to full boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir into fruit at once; stir 3 minutes.
Ladle into 2-cup glasses with lids.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Store in freezer.

title: muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Add salt and milk.
Sift baking powder and flour together; add to egg mixture, then add melted butter.
Cook in muffin pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook 2/3 cup water and
1 cup strawberries for 2 minutes. Blend in sugar
and cornstarch with remaining water.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Spread
cream
cheese
on pie
crust, fresh strawberries, then
cooked
mixture;
garnish with berries.
Other fruit can be used:
raspberries or blueberries.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Pour sauerkraut in colander and rinse; combine, then mix oil, vinegar, sugar and salt and pour over.
Let it set overnight.

title: toffee
directions: Combine ingredients in heavy skillet.
Stir constantly over medium heat until light amber in color (7 to 10 minutes).
This burns quickly!
Pour this hot candy over chopped nuts, spread on waxed paper.
Sprinkle with chocolate (I use milk chocolate) morsels, then spread chocolate over candy.
Sprinkle nuts on top of melted chocolate.
Let cool; break into pieces.
Eat!

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and run under cold water till it separates.
Mix all ingredients
together and pour into a large casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers browned in melted margarine.
Pour onto top of mixture and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
(May substitute cream of celery or cream of mushroom soup for chicken soup.)

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil Karo syrup, sugar, water and salt to hard ball stage. Add peanuts and cook until golden brown.
Remove from heat, add butter and baking soda.

title: 1-2-3 pickled red beets(optional: hard-boiled eggs)
directions: Drain beets (save juice).
Add water to juice to make 1 cup; to this add vinegar and
sugar; mix.
Pour over beets.
Cover and let set at least 24 hours (1 day).
Can add eggs anytime.

title: james' deer chili
directions: Cover meat with water.
Bring to simmer and add onion, salt and bell pepper.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Add chili powder, pepper or other spices to season to individual taste.
When seasoned to taste, make a liquid paste of cornstarch or flour to thicken to desired consistency.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook over slow heat until slow boil begins, stirring constantly.

title: green tomato crisp
directions: Slice the tomatoes. Soak 24 hours in 2 gallons water with
the lime.
Rinse well.
Put in ice water and let stand 3 hours. Cover with and soak overnight in the vinegar, sugar, salt, pickling spice and cloves. Bring to a boil. Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars and seal.
Makes about 12 pints.
(Recipe, 1960.)

title: cucumber salad
directions: Soak
cucumbers
in salt for 30 minutes and squeeze out water. Slice onions and add some celery seed if desired.	Put vinegar and
water	to
taste.
Add
sugar,
salt and pepper, enough to cover cucumbers
and onions.
Set in refrigerator to chill.

title: chicken breast
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with oregano, garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Dot each breast with butter. Pour wine in bottom of pan and baste as you cook.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into small balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Immediately top each cookie with a chocolate kiss, pressing it into dough.
Cool.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar gradually until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add coconut and vanilla flavors.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: bacon-cheese dip
directions: Add all of the ingredients together.
Mix well; chill.
Serve with Waverly crackers.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Mix soups, margarine (melted) and sour cream.
Pour over chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with stuffing.
Pour broth over stuffing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover for the last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake potatoes until soft.
Cut a slice off one side of each potato to make a long, boat shaped shell. Remove insides of potatoes; put through food mill.
Combine with 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon cream for each potato used; salt and pepper to taste.
Beat well.
Add 1 tablespoon parsley and 1 tablespoon chives per potato used; beat again.
Refill shells.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and dot with butter.
Return to oven long enough for potatoes to heat through and cheese to brown.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll 1 inch thick and slice. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 4 cups hot water.
Cool; add other ingredients and 2 quarts of water.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Pour off some grease and add mushrooms and onions.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add beef (cooked).
Stir in 1 1/2 cans tomato soup, water, oregano, salt and pepper.
Heat until boiling.
Cook macaroni.
Place into casserole in layers, meat, macaroni, then cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add chopped peppers if desired.

title: sunshine fish
directions: Mix together melted margarine, juice, grated rind, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Place filet on a piece of aluminum foil in a shallow baking dish.
Baste filet with sauce, using all of it. Fold foil over fish.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Using a fork, if fish flakes, it is done.
Do not overcook.
Yield:
1 filet for this mixture.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Roux:
Cook 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup bacon grease in a heavy pot slowly until brown; stir constantly.
Takes time; do not burn.

title: holiday corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart oblong baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix. Blend and pour over mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Better after it sits a while.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add seasoning mix, tomato sauce and water. Simmer 5 minutes.
Press crescent rolls into 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with 1 cup of crushed corn chips.
Cover with ground beef mixture.
Spread sour cream on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and add remaining corn chips.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave chocolate custard
directions: Using a wire whisk in a medium bowl, combine milks, chocolate syrup, sugar and cocoa.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
In separate bowl, whisk egg.
Add milk mixture while whisking.
Spray 4 custard cups with nonstick spray.
Put 1/4 mixture into each cup. Set cups in microwave dish.
Add enough water in dish until water is at same level as custard.
Microwave on Medium for 18 minutes, rotating baking dish 1/4 turn every 4 1/2 minutes until knife inserted in custard comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove cups from water bath.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.
Top with 1 tablespoon of whipped topping.
Serves 4. Contains 118 calories, 4 gm fat and 93 mg sodium.

title: kookie brittle
directions: Combine the oleo or butter, vanilla and salt. Beat in the sugar.
Add the flour.
Stir in the chocolate chips and peanuts. Pat firmly onto a 13 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon drops
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and peel until well combined.
Stir in flour mixture, mixing until smooth.
Refrigerate dough.
Cover 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer in large casserole dish the zucchini, bread crumbs, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni; ending with sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly and golden brown.

title: sesame pasta salad
directions: Cook linguine to al dente stage. Drain well and toss with remaining ingredients. Chill salad for several hours or overnight.

title: hurry-up soup
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 teaspoon sherry just before serving.

title: sunny day punch
directions: Combine punch and juices.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Serve over ice.
Makes 20 (8 ounce) servings.

title: no bake pineapple whipped cream cake
directions: Separate ladyfingers into single layer.
Line sides and bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Press them in firmly.
Whip cream until stiff.
In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese and sugar until well blended.

Fold cream cheese mixture into whipped cream. Spread 1/3 of whipped cream mixture, then 1/4 of pineapple pie filling; add a layer of ladyfingers on top of pie filling and repeat 2 more times with pie filling being last layer on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: texas hot chocolate cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Mix and bring to a boil the oleo, water, oil and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Mix buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and boil all ingredients.
Pour over spareribs with slices of onion and lemon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes a great buffet dish by adding cooked meatballs and chicken.

title: tomato cream salad
directions: Heat cheese and soup in double boiler. Dissolve the gelatin in cold water. Add cheese and soup to this while hot. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mold.

title: turkey cornbread stuffing
directions: Brown sausage and onion. Mix in a bowl remaining ingredients. Add sausage mixture to contents in bowl; mix well. Stuff turkey and cook as directed.

title: fudge cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
In saucepan, place butter or margarine, cocoa and water.
Bring to rapid boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture and mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and slightly beaten eggs.
Mix well; pour into greased pan (16 x 11-inch) or 2 small pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
(Batter will be thin.)
Start Fudge Icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: To prepare Burnt Sugar Syrup, put sugar in frying pan over fire until sugar softens, melts and begins to throw off smoke. Remove from fire and pour in boiling water quickly, allowing it to boil until it forms a molasses-like syrup.
Put aside.
This is sufficient for 3 cakes.

title: coconut peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet or use nonstick cookie sheet.
In a bowl, beat the eggs, milk, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Empty coconut from package onto a plate (for dipping).
Spread peanut butter evenly on each slice of bread.
Cut all 4 outer crust edges from each slice of bread and throw away (or feed to the birds).
Cut each slice of bread into 3 equal pieces ("finger" pieces).
Dip each piece in the egg batter; immediately dip in grated or flaked coconut.
Coat evenly on both sides.
Place on cookie sheet; bake until coconut turns light golden brown. Makes 30 "fingers."
Enjoy!!
Yum!!

title: tasting-is-believing chicken
directions: Remove the skin from all chicken parts.
Lightly brown the chicken and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine other ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking 15 minutes more.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: steamed meat dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients except wontons. Put 1 tablespoon filling in center of wonton. Fold 4 corners up to center and twist around filling. Steam for 15 to 20 minutes. Dip in 1 teaspoon lemon juice mixed with 1/4 cup soy sauce.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Whisk together thoroughly flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg in a large bowl then set aside.
Whisk together in another bowl the remaining ingredients except blueberries and add to the flour mixture.
Mix just until moistened.
Batter should not be smooth.
Fold in 1 1/2 c. fresh or frozen blueberries.
Divide the batter among the paper muffin cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for reserved butter and bread crumbs.
Put in well-greased casserole; sprinkle top with crumbs and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: onion frittata
directions: Heat olive oil in a heavy frying pan.
Add the onions.
Cook, stirring frequently, over lowest possible heat until the onions are soft and golden.
Stir the flour into the milk.
Combine with the eggs and beat to mix thoroughly.
Season with the salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour the egg mixture over the onions.
Cook until the Frittata is well set at the bottom and golden brown.
Put a plate, the size of the frying pan over the Frittata.
Turn the frying pan over so that the Frittata is on the plate, cooked side up.
Slide back into frying pan and cook until set.
Cut into wedges and serve hot or lukewarm.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix according to package directions. Pour into dish. Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk and the cream cheese together.
Mix the vanilla in, then add the lemon juice. Pour in pie shell, then put in refrigerator.

title: zuppa inglese(nancy's version)
directions: In food processor, blend well Ricotta, cream cheese, sour cream and eggs.
Mix in pudding (just add dry to the cheese mixture).
Add the Cool Whip.

title: eggless-milkless cake
directions: Combine the brown sugar, shortening or Nucoa, water, raisins or dates, salt, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon. Boil 3 minutes. Cool. Add the flour and baking powder. Add the soda mixture and nut meats.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° to 325°.
Set a pan of water in bottom of oven while baking.

title: mexican strata
directions: Spread
bread
cubes
evenly
in a 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish
that
has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Set aside. Beat
together
eggs,
skim
milk and yogurt.
Stir in cheeses and pour egg mixture over bread cubes in baking dish. Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Store in refrigerator.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Roll into 1-inch balls, then roll into a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: three layer dessert
directions: Mix one stick of butter (melted).
Flour and chopped nuts and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Than let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and about 1 to 2 cups of cool whip (just enough cool whip to make it easy to spread).
Mix 2 pkg of pudding with 3 1/2 c milk and vanilla.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto crust than spread pudding on top.
Use the remaining cool whip for the top layer.

title: king-size chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, cocoa and baking soda; mix until well blended.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Drop dough in 1/4 cup mounds onto greased cookie sheets about 3 inches apart.
Flatten each cookie slightly.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until set.
Cool slightly in pan, then remove to cooling rack.
Makes about 15 king-size cookies.

title: sour mustard pickles
directions: Pack a quart jar (or jars) with small cucumbers.
Add salt, sugar and mustard.
Fill the jar with vinegar.
Attach lid.
Set for two months before opening.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Bake in greased 9x13 pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake on cookie sheet covered with aluminum foil (bright side up).
Drop by scant 1/2 teaspoonfuls on foil, spacing approximately 4 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (time may vary from oven to oven).
Slide foil off sheet and let cool 5 minutes.
Lift cookies from foil by curling foil from bottom.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: strawberry nut bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
In bowl, combine strawberries, eggs and oil.
In separate bowl combine flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and nuts. Add strawberry mixture to dry ingredients and stir until blended. Pour batter into pans.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: skillet pizza
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix cornbread mix according to package directions.
Pour batter into skillet which has been greased and heated.
Cover batter with spaghetti sauce, then cover with hamburger meat and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes, or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bona zouf - german bean dish
directions: Cook beans 1/2 hour; then add 2 or 3 (according to size) diced potatoes and diced carrots.
Cut bologna in chunks.
When vegetables are done put 2 tablespoons Crisco in skillet and 3 tablespoons flour.
Stir and brown.
Now use some broth to make a gravy.
Be careful at first to be sure the water or broth is hot when adding to flour.
Now put it in with the beans and in 5 minutes cooking it's ready to eat.

title: sour cream-chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan, mixing well.
Heat until warm; do not boil.
Spoon a small amount of sauce into bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Fill tortillas with chicken sauce and cheese.
Roll up to enclose filling.
Arrange in a prepared dish.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.

title: golden fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, pineapple juice, lemon juice and orange juice.
Stir and boil for 1 minute.
Pour hot mixture over fruit. Leave uncovered, until cool.
Makes 25 to 35 servings.

title: white cake
directions: Beat egg whites until firm.
Blend sugar and Crisco.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla alternately with milk. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in two 8-inch pans lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool.
Frost with Baker's Icing.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a sheet pan.
Can use two 9-inch layer pans for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter well and pat into 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Beat eggs with sugar; mix in other ingredients.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: heather's kool-aid pops
directions: Note:
Fun for child to make on a hot summer day.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet and saute onions.
Mix in soup and milk.
Add chicken and cook until bubbly.
Line bottom of pan with chow mein noodles.
Add chicken and top with remaining chow mein noodles.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy hors d'oeuvres
directions: In a saucepan, melt currant jelly on low heat.
Add mustard. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add wieners; serve in fondue pot or crock-pot.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Add dry taco seasoning mix.
Let cool.
Cream together cream cheese and sour cream.
Add olives, cheese and chilies; mix well.
Add cooled hamburger and mix.
Spread mixture over tortilla shells.
Roll up and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate.
Cut into slices.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Combine corn meal, eggs, oil and corn in medium size bowl. Mix well.
Grease 8 x 8-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 400° until brown, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fat-free rich fudge brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Fold in Grape-Nuts, if desired.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan, sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Cool in pan.
Frost with chocolate version of no-fat cream cheese frosting.

title: quick ambrosia
directions: In bowl, mix first 7 ingredients. Top with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: chicken mix(deboning chicken isn't much trouble if you do it all at once)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle or Dutch oven.
Cover and cook over high heat until water boils.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from heat.
Strain broth and refrigerate until fat can be skimmed.
Cool chicken, then remove and discard bones and skin.
Put chicken into six 1-pint freezer containers, leaving 1/2-inch space at top.
Pour skimmed chicken broth into six more 1-pint containers, with 1/2-inch space at top. Seal and label containers.
Freeze.
Use within 3 months.
Makes about 6 pints of Chicken Mix and about 6 pints of Chicken Broth.

title: butter rum pound cake
directions: Cream
margarine,
Crisco
and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one
at
a	time, mixing thoroughly after each egg.
Add flavorings.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Sprinkle
crushed
pecans on the bottom of the pan. Add batter.
Put in cold oven.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Let stand overnight for best flavor.

title: honey-glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and quarter them. In a saucepan, cook carrots in boiling saltwater until tender. Drain thoroughly and allow to stand a few minutes to dry. In a skillet, heat the butter and honey; add carrots and simmer slowly, turning frequently until browned and glazed. Serves 4.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Arrange chicken in a greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Top with Swiss cheese. Combine soup and wine. Spoon over chicken. Sprinkle stuffing over mix. Drizzle butter over stuffing. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place washed chicken in baking pan. Bring the mixture to boil and pour over chicken. Cover with foil and cook for 1 1/2 hours or until tender at 300°.

title: heath torte
directions: Bake a devil's food cake according to the package directions. Cool, then split the layers, using thread.

title: quick casserole
directions: Combine ingredients except cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 3/4 stick oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream 1 1/2 sticks oleo and the eggs.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar; beat 20 minutes.
Spread this mixture on cracker crumbs.
Layer drained pineapple on creamed mixture. Peel and cut bananas into strips and layer over pineapple.
Mix Dream Whip according to package; top over bananas.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix well.
Spread in an 11 x 15-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: self-crust egg custard
directions: Mix flour and eggs.
Add to well beaten eggs.
Add milk, evaporated milk, melted butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Grease 9-inch pie pan with butter.
Pour mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for approximately 40 minutes.
Pie will rise while baking, but will fall while cooling.

title: night on the town wieners
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer in covered casserole for 4 to 6 hours at 250° in oven or all day, covered, in a crock-pot on low.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix tomato soup with ground beef, rice, egg, onion, parsley and salt.
Shape into balls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter (about 16).

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: peanut butter cake(with chocolate peanut butter icing)
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: orange blush
directions: Combine undiluted orange juice, cranberry juice and sugar. Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, stir in club soda and pour over crushed ice.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: While rice is cooking, pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Using large skillet, brown meat in butter. Add garlic and broth. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and peppers.
Cover and cook 5 more minutes. Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce. Stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring, until clear and thick, about 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and other vegetables.
Stir gently.
Heat until all vegetables are hot. Serve over fluffy rice.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place ingredients in greased 2 1/2 qt. baking dish in the order given. A layer of potatoes, celery, hamburger, green pepper, tomatoes, onions, salt and pepper. Bake the casserole covered at 375° for first ten minutes. Uncover and continue baking for one hour. You may half the recipe.

title: spaghetti
directions: Mix hamburger meat, bell pepper, garlic salt and onion together.
Brown, then add tomatoes and tomato paste; mix and add 1 tomato paste can of water.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cook spaghetti and drain.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed and let jell.
Beat and add all other ingredients to Jell-O.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: yankee chili
directions: * Example:
1 teaspoon chili pepper, 1 teaspoon paprika, 1 teaspoon seasoned pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.

title: peanut butter icing for banana cake
directions: In a small bowl beat softened cream cheese and corn syrup until smooth.
Add peanut butter and beat until well blended. Spread on cooled cake.
Garnish with chopped peanuts.

title: old-fashioned apple stack cake
directions: Cream molasses and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together twice; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Chill dough.

title: amigo dip
directions: Blend avocados, cream cheese, sour cream, milk, lemon juice, and chili powder together in food processor or blender until creamy.
Spread the mixture on the bottom of a large platter. Then top with remaining ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve. This appetizer may also be converted into individual salads for a mexican dinner.
Try using small terra cotta or ceramic dishes for each layered salad surrounding each with a circle of chips. Garnish with a slice of lime, or a bit of fresh cilantro.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain well.
Mix all ingredients together in large kettle and simmer to blend flavors. May add to each bowl:
corn chips, grated cheese, sour cream, olives, or anything else you may like.

title: money salad
directions: Mix all together; refrigerate overnight.
Especially great in summertime or anytime.

title: enola's saucepan p.b. cookies
directions: Mix Karo and sugar in medium saucepan. Bring mixture to a full rolling boil.
(Do not cook.)
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter. Add corn flakes and mix well without mashing flakes.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Makes 40 to 50.

title: deluxe chicken breasts
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Roll in flour to coat both sides. Fry in hot Crisco oil until breasts are brown on both sides. Place chicken breasts in large baking dish with thick side down. Mix soups and broth well in large bowl.
Pour over chicken, covering all breasts well.
Add chopped onion and sliced peppers on the top of chicken.
Cover with foil and cook in 375° oven for about 40 minutes (depending on the size of the chicken).

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour together in a large bowl.
Mix applesauce, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, baking soda and shortening together in another large bowl.
Combine the sugar mixture and applesauce mixture.
Add raisins and chopped nuts.
Put the mixed ingredients into a greased angel food cake pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Add sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, allspice and ginger to apples in crock-pot.
Cook 24 hours on low, stirring occasionally. Run through the blender, then put back in the crock-pot to reheat.
Sterilize jars.
Fill with apple butter and seal.
Put in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: ed's cod av vin
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Use it to flour chicken. Melt butter in a large pan.
Brown the chicken well, then add the wine (enough to cover the chicken).
Cover and let simmer for about 50 minutes.
Drain mushrooms and add to chicken a few minutes before serving.
Serve with baked potatoes, tossed salad, hot French bread and wine.

title: mrs. fields chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars, add eggs and vanilla. Blend the 5 c. oatmeal in a blender until fine, add flour, salt, baking powder, soda, add to cream mixture.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes. Underbake will make them chewy. About 112 cookies.

title: cake
directions: Mix the ingredients with the drained fruit.
Bake in a tube or Bundt pan for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: eagle brand lemon pie
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and rind.
Mix with hand mixer on low.
Blend in egg yolks.
Turn into crust.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours, then top with Cool Whip.

title: grandma janie's best peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, 1/2 cup of the sugar, 3/4 cup of the butter and the vanilla in a heavy pot over medium heat.
Lower to simmer and melt the butter.
Stir the 1/3 cup of flour into the 3/4 cup of water in a small bowl until smooth.
Stir this paste into the peaches.

title: beefy-veggie casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together; drain off fat.
Add soup, spaghetti and Veg-All.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with your favorite grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one dish pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 13 x 9-inch casserole or pan with foil, leaving enough on top to fold and seal.
Place pork chops on bottom and arrange potatoes, onions, bell pepper, carrots and celery around sides of dish.
Mix Worcestershire sauce and sherry together and pour over chops.
Sprinkle soup mix over entire dish.
Cut butter and distribute over contents of dish. Fold and seal the foil.
Bake for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender and pork chops are done.
Season to taste.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Great for a "make ahead" meal.

title: festive ice
directions: You also need 2 plastic ice cube trays.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in square cake pan or dish. Freeze solid.
Set out for a few minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: reese's ice cream pie
directions: Mix ice cream and peanut butter.
Put into pie shell and freeze.

title: gram's quick sticky buns
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch pan.
Drizzle in honey.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn out on large plate.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While hot, make topping.

title: minty cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sugar and chopped mint; cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, add pineapple to cottage cheese mixture; spoon into a lettuce lined bowl.
Top with orange sections; garnish with fresh mint sprigs.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and butter on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Put into buttered pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil carrots a couple minutes; add zucchini and onion.
Boil until carrots are nearly done, not mushy.
Drain.
Mix soup and sour cream; add to vegetables.
Butter casserole; melt small amount of oleo and mix with croutons or Stove Top.
Put half of this in casserole.
Add soup and vegetable mix.
Top with rest of croutons or Stove Top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: quick banana bread
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly combine biscuit mix, sugar, flour and baking soda.
Combine eggs and sour cream, stir into dry ingredients and mashed bananas.
Stir in chopped nuts, pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350 for 50 minutes or until done. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely on wire rack.

title: apple ketchup
directions: Chop vegetables in blender or processor.
Cook all ingredients about 30 minutes after it begins to boil.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Delicious.

title: berry-mandarin tossed salad
directions: In a 2-cup microwavable bowl, combine sugar, vinegar, honey, lemon juice, paprika, mustard, onion, celery seed and salt. Microwave uncovered on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Whisk in oil.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
In salad bowl, combine greens, strawberries, oranges, onion, almonds and bacon.
Drizzle with dressing and gently toss to coat.
Yield: 12 to 14 servings.

title: "diet" shake
directions: Put everything in blender, be sure top is secure.
Blend until smooth and fluffy.

title: fruit flavored float
directions: Combine sugar and drink mix.
Add milk; stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour mixture into 8 tall glasses.
Spoon about 1/2 cup of the ice cream into each glass.
Slowly pour in the chilled carbonated water to fill each glass.
Stir gently to mix.
(Or, mix and serve in a large punch bowl.)
Makes about 8 (8 ounce) servings.

title: heritage chicken and rice
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine rice, broth, parsley, pimentos, salt and butter; stir well.
Combine garlic salt, paprika and celery salt.
Rub over chicken.
Place chicken in rice. `Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender and rice is tender.
Makes six servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until well mixed.
Add cream.
Then add sugar and other ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into an 8-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: graham biscuits
directions: *May use whole wheat flour instead of graham flour.

title: mardi gras seafood casserole
directions: Prepare rice, then stir in sour cream, salt, chiles and cheese. Mix well. Add seafood; mix again. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with paprika. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop on a greased tin.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients except flour and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in flour, one cup at a time.
Turn out on floured surface and knead.
Cut or form biscuits.
Oil pan slightly and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Put into scalded jars and seal.

title: tomato and cucumber salad
directions: Combine the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, black pepper and parsley in a jar and shake until thoroughly mixed.
Pour over tomatoes, cucumbers and onions.
Marinate 2 hours before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: tarragon chicken breasts
directions: In a skillet, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add shallots. Saute for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms; saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove vegetables; keep warm.

title: sour cream corn casserole
directions: Stir together and pour into casserole dish, sprayed with Pam. Reserve 1 cup grated cheese and 2 tablespoons peppers. Sprinkle cheese and peppers on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in bowl the bananas (well mashed), eggs and butter.
Stir together flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Add to banana mixture.
Add nuts and stir well.
Place in greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5-inches).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kielbasa and beans
directions: In skillet cook sausage; stir in onion and peppers. Cook and stir until sausage is lightly browned and vegetables are tender. Combine brown sugar, steak sauce, vinegar and worcestershire sauce. Stir into skillet and add beans. Cook and heat through while stirring.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet and bake according to directions until done, about 10 minutes; cool. Cream together the cream cheese, Miracle Whip, onion flakes, garlic powder and dill weed. Spread on cooled crust. Chop broccoli, green and red peppers, cauliflower, carrots, radishes, celery and black olives. Sprinkle on cream cheese and press in. Top with grated cheese. Chill and serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Add eggs, onion, cheese and salad dressing. Add pepper and celery salt to taste.
May use 1/4 to 1/2 cup chopped celery instead of celery salt.
If too dry, add more salad dressing.

title: valerie's green beans, italian style
directions: Place the frozen beans into 10-inch skillet with the oil, garlic, parsley, sugar, salt and pepper. Cook, covered, over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add the broth and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until beans are almost tender.
Raise heat to moderate, add the tomato slices and cook, uncovered, for another 5 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
May use 1 quart half and half for 1 quart milk.
Place in canister of ice cream maker.
Pack according to maker's directions.
Serve with warm blanket.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Mix meat, milk, oatmeal, pepper, chili powder, garlic powder, salt and eggs until well blended.
Shape into walnut-size balls. Place in a large roasting pan.
Top with a sauce made of catsup, brown sugar, liquid smoke, garlic powder and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Freezes well.
Can be used as an entree with rice.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Combine water, vegetables and seasoning in large pan.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Make white sauce with oleo, flour and milk; add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add corn and undrained vegetables.
Heat.
Do not boil.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Combine flours and add alternately with milk, being sure last addition is flour.
Add flavorings.
Beat, then stir in nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bran muffins for 4
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Measure cereal and milk together into small mixing bowl. Stir to combine.
Let stand for 1 or 2 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Add shortening.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring until combined.
Portion batter evenly into four greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Bake in oven at 400° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 4 muffins.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Place in large bowl.
Add lettuce, radishes, basil, vinaigrette and cheese.
Mix and chill before serving. Yield: 6 servings.

title: squash relish
directions: Chop fine.
Cover with ice water and ice.
Add 1/2 cup salt. Let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Rinse well under cold running water. Drain again and set aside.
Boil sugar, vinegar, turmeric and celery seed for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pour solution over squash mixture.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage in skillet, then drain.
Add red pepper flakes, oregano and garlic salt.
Cube the Velveeta and add to mixture.
Spread on the party rye.
Fast freeze on cookie sheets.
Put on tray under broiler for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients by hand, like meat loaf.
Makes 32 balls.

title: fitty's dressing
directions: Mix dressing.
Toss salad with it and serve over salad.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry onion and ground beef (if desired) until tender.
Add tomato sauce and paste, then water.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 2 hours.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash, drain, cut okra into pieces.
In large zip lock bag add, flour, corn meal, salt, and pepper.
Place drained okra into bag and shake well to coat each piece.
Dump okra out of bag into colander and shake off excess mixture.
Place oil in large skillet and heat on medium heat to melt.
Place okra into skillet and fry, stirring often to keep for sticking, fry until golden brown.

title: cinnamon chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa, Crisco and water to boil in small saucepan.
Pour over flour and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients, beating well.
Pour into a greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar and Karo in a boiler over medium-high heat.
As the mixture comes to a boil, remove from heat.
Mix in 12 ounces of peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add 6 cups of cornflakes and mix well. Drop onto waxed paper.
Makes about 32.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, flour, water, nuts and vanilla. Measure 1 teaspoon, roll and shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Roll in sifted powdered sugar while cookies are still warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: crazy cake
directions: Stir together dry ingredients; sift. Make a hole in the center of this and add the rest of the ingredients. Beat together with a spoon and mix well. Bake in loaf or layer pan, greased & floured, at 350° for 30 minutes, or until toothpick comes out dry when inserted. Frost as desired.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Blend 2 tablespoons sugar with cornstarch.
Add pineapple. Cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Cool.
Blend softened cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Add eggs one at a time. Stir well after each.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Spread cooled pineapple over bottom of shell.
Pour in cream cheese mixture and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 325° for another 50 minutes.
Serve at room temperature.
Do not refrigerate.

title: lemony nut bread
directions: Beat sugar and butter until light; add lemon peel.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and juice; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to batter. Add nuts.
Mix until just blended.
Turn into two greased and floured loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes or until done.
Cool on rack.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Garnish with roses if desired.

title: date nut tarts
directions: Shells:
Soften cream cheese and 2 sticks of margarine.
Mix in flour.
Chill.
Divide into thirds.
Roll out one section until thin and cut into rounds with a regular biscuit cutter.
Fit into small muffin tins.
The dough doesn't come to the top of tins.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Wash berries.
Cover with water.
Add sugar and butter; bring to boil
and
drop
dumpling
on top of boiling mixture. Boil for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with remaining
dough.
Slice margarine on top.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at
for
20 minutes.
Turn oven on broil to brown top.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box; add carrots and walnuts. Bake cake as directed on back of box.
When cool, frost with frosting and sprinkle with nuts.

title: nutty carrot cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; blend in eggs, carrots and vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Frost with Vanilla Frosting.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut into strips or small slices. Simmer, covered in boiling salted water OR steam until crisp-tender. Melt the butter; stir in brown sugar until dissolved. Add carrots. Cook over medium-low heat turning often to coat. Sprinkle with snipped parsley.

title: baked flounder(serves 6)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Season fish with salt and pepper.
Mix juice and margarine.
Dip fish into margarine mixture.
Place in a greased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Pour remaining margarine mix over fish.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chocolate cookies 2
directions: Mix all ingredients. Place in greased 15 x 10 inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool and cut into bars.

title: hugs and kisses cookies(yield: 4 dozen cookies)
directions: 1. Stir sugar, condensed milk and peanut butter together in large bowl.
Stir in Bisquick and vanilla extract.

title: peppermint dessert
directions: Crush 30 Oreo cookies or use boxed crumbs.
Put 2/3 of cookie crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix with 1/3 cup melted oleo.
Pat evenly on bottom of pan.
Add the peppermint ice cream, layered on top of cookie crumbs; freeze.
Spread hot fudge topping and freeze.
It is easier to spread the topping if jar is heated first.
Add Cool Whip; spread on top.
Sprinkle top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: red devil punch
directions: Wrap
the cloves, allspice and cinnamon in cheesecloth. Put all ingredients in a pot or large percolator.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and peanut butter together.
Blend in Cool Whip slowly.
Pour into graham cracker shell and chill.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until done.
Let cool and then ice.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour over chopped cabbage and green pepper; mix thoroughly.
Chill.

title: mary's cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in
water.
Add salt, sugar, water and 4 cups of the
flour;
beat
with	a
fork
until bubbly and let stand, covered until double in bulk.
Add eggs, sugar and oil; blend well.
Add	rest of flour.	Knead on floured board until smooth. Divide in
half,
roll out.
Sprinkle well with sugar and cinnamon after
spreading
with butter.
Roll up and slice into 1-inch slices.
Place
on	greased
cookie
sheet and let rise until double.
Bake
at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen rolls.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients except pasta, in a soup pot.
Cook pasta, then add to mixture.
Add enough milk to make soup as thick or as thin as you like.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: oven "fried" salmon cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all together; shape into patties, about 8.
Bake on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with nonfat coating for about 8 to 10 minutes to brown.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Stir jello, boiling water, vinegar and salt until Jell-O is completely dissolved.
Refrigerate until mixture mounds slightly (approximately 20 to 30 minutes).
Stir in next 3 ingredients. Pour into mold and refrigerate until set, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy rice pizza
directions: Press rice, 1/2 cup cheese and egg evenly in a 9-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 450°
for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine basil, oregano, tomato sauce and salt.
Heat in saucepan until hot.
Spread evenly over rice crust.
Top with sliced pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: spicy peach shortcake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
With a fork, stir in buttermilk just until blended.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Knead 3 to 5 times.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into an 8-inch round.
Put one round on a cookie sheet. Brush with melted butter.
Top with remaining round.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and put together with whipped cream and peaches.
Serves 8.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cheddar cheese.
Grease casserole dish, add mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes more. Serve hot.
Use tortilla chips to dip into beans.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and add cooked chicken, spaghetti, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Mix all together and season to taste with celery salt and Mrs. Dash.
Place in a baking dish and pour chicken broth around edges and over the top.
Bake at 325° until it thickens. Just before removing from oven, cover with grated cheese.

title: polish gherkin soup(serves 4)
directions: Dice all pickles from jar into 1/4-inch pieces.
Saute onions in margarine until wilted.
Add carrots and potatoes and saute until brown.
Stir to heat through, then add chicken stock or bouillon cubes and water.
Add pickles and 1/2 cup brine.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add 1 cup cream and season to taste.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Cook chicken pieces in a large pot of water until tender. Remove bones if chicken with bones is used. Saut onion in margarine. Add seasonings and chicken. Saut about 10 minutes longer. Add sour cream and mix well. Add Dumplings and mix well. Heat through and serve. Serves 8.

title: peanut butter chocolate bonbons
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Melt peanut butter and margarine together, then pour the first 4 ingredients over until well moistened and shape in balls.
Spear balls with toothpicks and dip and place on wax paper until set.

title: crescent city cheesecake
directions: *Low-fat products may be substituted for cream cheese and sour cream.

title: rice dressing
directions: Saute ground meat, onion, bell pepper and celery leaves.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in pot with tight lid.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: short crust pastry
directions: Rub the fat and flour together using the fingertips until no lumps remain visible.
Add the cold water, a little at a time, until the dough is smooth and firm.

title: can't stop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add dry ingredients, then fold in cornflakes and nuts.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peach crunch
directions: Place peaches in baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix flour, sugar and egg until lumpy.
Spread mix over peaches. Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.
Serves 6.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Combine
the
3 ingredients and mix well.
Press firmly into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes, or for an unbaked crust, chill 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugars and milk until soft ball stage, then add peanut butter, vanilla and butter.
Beat until stiff.
Put in buttered pan.

title: minestrone milanese
directions: Put olive oil in large kettle.
Add garlic, onion, leek, parsley and thyme and cook until soft.
Add tomato paste, thinned with water and cook for 5 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients except rice, beans and cheese.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Bring to boil.
Add rice and cook until soft.
Add beans; heat. Serve with cheese.
Makes 3 quarts or 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip ice cream pie
directions: Coat sides of 8-inch pie dish.
Combine syrup and chips.
Heat until hot.
Combine remaining chocolate and cereal.
Pat in pie dish.
Freeze firm.
Combine other half of chocolate mix and sour cream.
Mix well.
Spread half the ice ream on frozen pie crust. Layer again and freeze.

title: cheddar cheese dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sour cream, onion, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce at highest speed of mixer until well blended. Gradually add 1 cup cheese and continue beating at high speed until smooth.
Fold in remaining cheese.
Serve immediately or allow to reach room temperature before serving.
Serve with onion sticks or crackers.

title: apple wok cakes
directions: Combine flour, milk, salt and egg yolks.
Mix thoroughly.
Add apples.
Beat
egg	whites	until stiff, but not dry. Fold in the apple
mixture.
Preheat a wok and add the vegetable oil.
Heat over
high	heat
until
oil
begins to smoke. Reduce
heat to medium.
Gently
drop
heaping
spoonfuls
of batter 1 to 2 at
a time
so
the cakes are about 4-inches in diameter.
Brown one side,
then
turn
and brown other side. Remove from pan. Sprinkle with sugar.
Serve warm.

title: jiffy hot rolls
directions: Mix together water and yeast.
Mix in remaining ingredients and let rise until it is double the size.
Stir down and spoon in greased muffin tins.
Let rise again and bake at 400° until brown. Butter the tops of rolls.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: yankee turkey dressing
directions: Saute chopped celery in butter.
Add parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder and poultry seasoning; heat.
Mix with very dry bread crumbs.
Add cream of chicken soup and chicken broth.
Mix to a soft moist consistency.
Bake until set and lightly browned.

title: casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown hamburger, sausage and onion. Drain well; mix in soups and noodles.
Top with grated cheese and bake until bubbly at 350°.
This recipe will serve 12 people.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine bread crumbs and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Beat egg.
Put in a shallow bowl.
Dip chicken in egg, then in crumb mixture.

title: corn-broccoli casserole
directions: Combine first six ingredients and seasoning in greased casserole.
Blend 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken ole
directions: Layer tortillas on bottom of a large baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients, except cheese.
Pour over tortillas.
Top with cheese. Bake in a 375° oven about 25 minutes.

title: beefy tomato stroganoff
directions: Microwave:
In 2-quart casserole, thoroughly combine all ingredients.
Microwave uncovered at High for 14 minutes or until noodles are tender; stir.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped fresh parsley.
Makes about 2 servings.

title: snacks
directions: Mix last four ingredients and pour over crackers.
Toss until all of the oil is taken up.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix all together; cream butter.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: oven barbecue
directions: Cut meat lengthwise (not all the way through).
Place in rectangular baking dish.
Place potatoes around it.
Mix sauce and pour over it.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Make a tossed salad and you have a complete meal.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and fruit filling.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Allow cream cheese, sour cream and butter to come to room temperature. In a large bowl, blend all ingredients, except eggs. Beat in eggs one at a time and mix well. Pour mixture into a greased 10-inch spring pan. Place in a larger pan with 1/2-inch water in it. Bake at 375° for about 1 hour. Remove form pan of water carefully and cool. Put your favorite topping on when serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a bowl, combine sauerkraut, celery, green pepper and onion. Mix sugar, vinegar and oil; stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Cover and chill mixture for 3 to 24 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: braunschweiger spread
directions: Stir together and make a mold or ball.
If you wish to frost the ball, you will need 1 more 8 ounce package of cream cheese. Make a day ahead as it is a bit bitter if used immediately.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in covered casserole for 40 minutes at 350°.
Then uncover and top with cracker crumbs or almonds and corn flake crumbs.
Then bake for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put eggs in blender with onion, salt, flour, baking powder and 1/2 c. cubed potatoes. Cover, process at liquefy until smooth. Add remaining potatoes; cover and process two cycles at grind. Pour onto hot well greased griddle. Drain on absorbent paper. Yield 12 pancackes.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: About
hour	before	serving
or
early
in the day: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon,
salt,
baking soda, baking powder and ginger.
In a large bowl,
with
a wire whisk or fork, mix shredded carrots, yogurt,
egg
substitute, applesauce, raisins, brown sugar and vanilla
extract until well-blended.
With a spoon, stir flour mixture
into
carrot
mixture
just until flour is moistened. Spoon batter
into bake cups in a muffin tin.
Bake 30 minutes or until
a
toothpick inserted in center of each muffin comes out clean.
Makes
muffins.
Each muffin:
About 124 calories, 0 g fat, 1/2 mg cholesterol and 196 mg sodium.

title: almost heaven cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan or baking dish.
Remove from oven and prick generously with fork.
Pour pineapple over top while cake is hot.
Blend pudding with milk and beat in cream cheese.
Spread over pineapple, then cover with whipped topping.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
