directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Save 4 cups of juice from the fruits.
Mix all fruit together in large bowl.
Mix together fruit juice, Tang and dry pudding mix.
Pour over fruit and mix well.
Refrigerate 6 hours before serving.
Serve with angel food cake.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly by hand; form into balls. Place on wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip in chocolate; place on wax paper to dry.

title: party fritos
directions: Melt butter over low heat and add m.s.g., stirring to mix. Pour over Fritos in a large bowl and stir to coat.
Dust with lots of Parmesan cheese, stirring to coat again.
Spread on a large cookie sheet, layer thick.
Toast until medium brown in a 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Keep in a tin box.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients to the first mixture.
Chill dough. Roll spoon sized dough into balls and roll through cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix and margarine, then add one egg.
Spread onto bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Add confectioners sugar.
Pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Refrigerate for a while, then cut into squares.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Slice up orange slices and break up nuts.
Mix all flour, sugar and baking powder.
Put chopped nuts and orange slices in 1/2 of flour mixture.
Mix top half ingredients real good so orange slices won't stick.
Add eggs which are slightly beaten. Add rest of flour mixture.
Add lemon extract.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch flat cake pan.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: angel wings
directions: Brown chicken lightly in half the butter in skillet and season with salt and pepper.
Lay in single layer in greased shallow baking dish.
Splash with about 1/4 cup chicken broth.
Cover tightly and bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
While chicken bakes, heat onion gently in remaining butter in same pan until soft and golden.
Rinse dry and seed peppers.
Dice and add to pan with garlic and flour.
Stir and cook a minute or so.
Stir in the broth (add broth from chicken to measure 1 cup).
Stir over low heat until smooth, creamy and slightly thickened.
Pour into blender and whirl until pureed.
Put back in skillet and add cream.
Heat to simmering and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is heated through and cheese is glazed.

title: icing for gingerbread house
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add powdered sugar slowly.
When mixed, add tartar and vanilla.
Use icing to put graham crackers around a milk carton.
Decorate with candy canes, M&M's, etc.

title: navy shrimp and curry
directions: Cook and clean shrimp.
Cook rice.
Keep hot.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Melt butter in double boiler top over direct heat.
Add onion; simmer until tender.
Stir in the next 5 ingredients, then slowly stir in bouillon and milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened.
Add shrimp and lemon juice; heat.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, then jam.
Put spices with flour.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavoring, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, light brown sugar and Kahlua together with beater.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Dip strawberries, bananas or any fruit.

title: italian marinade
directions: Add all ingredients in mixing bowl and whisk. Great on grilled veggies.

title: chicken broth
directions: Mix and heat about 15 minutes.
Simmer (to taste).

title: polish spaghetti
directions: Combine following ingredients into large saucepan: sausage (cut into 2-inch pieces), 32 ounces of sauce, onion and bell pepper.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Prepare spaghetti according to instructions.
Serve spaghetti on plate and cover with sauce.

title: baked fish fillets(in wine sauce)
directions: Season fillets with salt.
Place in Corning Ware baking dish in which you have melted the butter, oil, parsley flakes and onion. Simmer about 15 minutes after adding wine.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half of mixture in well-greased hot skillet (iron is best).
Sprinkle half of cheese over corn bread mixture.
Pour rest of corn bread over cheese. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicketti(or chicken cacciatore)
directions: Cook hen until tender, remove bones and dice.
Add water to broth to make 2 quarts.
Add onion and cook for a few minutes. Add spaghetti and cook 20 minutes.
Add celery, pimento and soup, stirring occasionally while adding ingredients; cook a few minutes.
Add chicken, season to taste with salt and pepper and cook longer, stirring from bottom.
Place in casserole and cover with grated cheese.
Brown in oven about 30 minutes.
Will serve 10 to 15 people.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, salt and sugar. Cool to lukewarm. Add egg and yeast, then add flour. Pinch off pieces of dough and place in well-greased pans and bake at 375°.

title: mushroom-chicken saute
directions: Season chicken.
Chop onions and garlic.
Saute in oil and soy sauce.
Add chicken to pan and saute lightly.
Add flour, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Cover and let simmer on low heat for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: party casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in milk and cheese until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Grate carrots and boil for 2 minutes. Drain. Grate onions. Place raw hamburger in bowl. Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Mix well. Take wrappers and lay out. Fold into triangle. Then fold corners and top down. Deep-fry for 20 to 25 minutes at 250°.

title: onion-cheese-bacon spread
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add onion to mayonnaise.
Add cream cheese to remaining ingredients.
Spread on Melba toast.

title: granny's orange mint drink(delightful summer drink)
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar is dissolved (about 5 to 10 minutes).
Add juices and orange rind.
Pour hot mixture over mint and let it steep 1 hour.
Strain.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix together all but 6 tablespoons sugar and 3 tablespoons cinnamon.
Peel and slice 4 to 6 apples.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon together.
Layer in greased tube pan, starting with one-third batter, cinnamon mixture, half apples, cinnamon mixture, one-third batter; repeat, ending with last one-third batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Leave in pan to cool.

title: meatballs
directions: Form hamburger into small balls about 1 inch in diameter. Brown meatballs; pour out grease.
Combine chicken soup, water and onion soup.
Pour over meatballs.
Stir well and turn heat down. Simmer about 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or potatoes.
Serves approximately 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to boil; stir until clear and thick.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello.
Bake 9-inch pie shell.
Cut up fresh strawberries and add to jello mixture.
Pour in baked pie shell; chill and serve with whipped topping.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix and press into a loaf pan or dish.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Pour 1 stick melted butter over crackers until all crumbs are buttered.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Return to oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta delight
directions: Cook and drain penne pasta.
Cook and stir zucchini in hot oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to medium. Add shallots and garlic; cook 1 minute.
Add tomato; cook and stir 40 seconds.
Add basil and cheese.
Pour vegetable mixture over penne in large bowl; toss gently to mix.

title: apricot-pineapple gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O
and
marshmallows
in
cups boiling water. Drain juice
from
apricots;
adding
enough
water to make 2 cups.
Add
to
Jell-O
mixture and chill until shakes. Drain pineapple; reserve juice for topping.
Dice apricots and add with pineapple to Jell-O.
Chill until firm in 9 x 13-inch dish. Spread with topping, garnish with chopped nuts.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together and top with crumbs that have been mixed with oleo.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 baking sheets.
In a medium saucepan, heat butter, water and salt to boiling over high heat. As soon as butter melts, remove from heat.
Add flour.
Beat vigorously until smooth.
Over medium heat, stir 30 seconds until ball forms.
Cool 3 minutes.
Beat in eggs one at a time, beating until dough is smooth between additions.
Drop dough onto prepared baking sheets 2 inches apart and brush with egg yolk water mixture. Do not drip onto baking sheet.
Bake dough 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 minutes or until very crisp.
Remove and cool on rack.
Cut in half crosswise and fill.
I prefer a vanilla custard filling.

title: roasted red pepper jelly
directions: Follow manufacturer's instructions to prepare canning jars, lids and bands.
To roast peppers, cut in half lengthwise and remove seeds and membranes.
Place skin side up on an ungreased baking sheet; flatten with hand.
Broil about 3 inches from heat about 15 to 20 minutes until peppers are blackened and charred. Immediately seal peppers in a plastic bag and allow to steam 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove charred skin.

title: sauce for seafood
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill and serve.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Put broccoli, onion, celery, green peppers and rice in bowl and blend together.
Put soup, Cheez Whiz and butter in casserole dish and heat until butter is melted.
Add the rest of the mixture to casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine all ingredients in a two quart casserole dish, except 1/2 cheese and 1/2 onions.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake 5 more minutes.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in frig overnight. Roll thin for fried pies. Will keep in frig for long time.

title: 10 bean soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in large stock pot.
Cook for 2 1/2 hours.
Add pepper, tomato paste and pasta.
Cook additional 1/2 hour.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Equal amounts (1 teaspoon of each).

title: grandma bundt's dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put pineapple and juice in bottom of pan. Put cherry pie filling on top of pineapple.
Mix butter with dry cake mix and sprinkle on top, then add nuts.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Serve cool with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: snickers pie
directions: Butter an 8-inch pie plate.
In a medium bowl, combine the graham cracker crumbs and 1 tablespoon of sugar; stir in the butter until well combined.
Press the crumb mixture into the bottom and sides of pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes or until set.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: pinwheels
directions: Spray 8 or 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray. Spread on bottom and sides of pan with a paper towel.
Mix gelatin and water in 1 1/2 to 2 quart microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.* Stir to dissolve completely.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and milk.
Fold in cherries, pecans and whipped cream.
Pour into 9-inch graham cracker pie crust.
Make day before.

title: sweet potato nut log
directions: Mash sweet potatoes in a large mixing bowl.
Blend in margarine, salt, flour and sugar.
Form into logs and roll in chopped pecans.
Place in a greased, shallow pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix sour cream, cheese and soup together.
Crumble corn flakes on top of pan of potatoes after spreading cheese, soup and sour cream mixture. Then on top of corn flakes, melt 1 to 1 1/2 cups margarine or butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and slightly browned on top.

title: slaw to freeze
directions: Add salt to cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
Then squeeze out. Add carrot and pepper.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mash cream cheese in a bowl.
Add sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Top with strawberries or berries of choice.
Chill for 45 minutes before eating.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Drain juice from cocktail.
Dissolve soda and salt in juice.
Mix dry and wet ingredients together. Bake in greased pan for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: speedy chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine peanut butter and chocolate syrup. Stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll each ball in finely chopped peanuts, pecans, walnuts or coconut; chill 1 hour.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Combine the wafer crumbs, brown sugar and butter; set aside. Combine the eggs, vanilla, lemon juice, salt and applesauce. Blend thoroughly and pour in pie crust.
Top with crumb mixture. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Boil 1 cup water.
Dissolve the cherry jello.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Refrigerate until thick.
Add pineapple, orange, walnuts and cranberries.
Mix into jello and put into greased mold to harden.
When releasing mold, loosen edges with a table knife and set into hot water and count to ten.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening until size of peas. Add buttermilk and then yeast mixture.
Stir until flour is dampened.
Knead on floured surface.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: mock champagne
directions: Stir ingredients together in a pitcher.
Makes 17 (4 ounce) servings.

title: poinsettia balls
directions: 1. Melt 1 pkg. german sweet chocolate and 3 Tbsp. butter over low heat and stir.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; beat with an electric mixer until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into pastry shell; bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Marinate French-cut beans and bean sprouts overnight in the following:
sugar, vinegar, oil and garlic salt.
Put sliced almonds on top.
Heat in oven once before serving.
May be served cold also.
Keeps for days.

title: "fanny mae fudge"
directions: In a double boiler melt butter; add sugar and milk.
Stir until warm; add marshmallows.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Turn off; add all chocolate and stir until melted. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.

title: sweet sour chicken
directions: Mix and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate for 24 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Place cherry pie filling and pineapple with juice in bottom of pan; mix well.
Sprinkle cake mix over the top of this mixture. Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° to 400° until brown.

title: chile and cheese appetizer tart
directions: Allow both crust pouches to stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes.
While waiting have a cold beer or glass of wine. While drinking, turn on your oven to 450°.

title: fairy pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter together and add egg yolks, milk, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat well.
Place in two greased layer tins.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread over dough in each tin.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 325° until meringue turns slightly brown.
Drain pineapple juice.
Mix whipped cream and pineapple together.
Turn over layer upside-down with meringue at the bottom.
Spread with pineapple and whipped cream.
Place other layer with meringue on top.

title: finger salad or vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls in a large baking dish or a jelly roll pan and bake until done to form your crust.
Combine cream cheese, salad dressing and dressing mix with a small amount of milk to a spreading consistency.
Spread on baked and cooled crust.
Arrange your choice of vegetables on top and sprinkle with grated cheese. Chill.

title: chocolate covered raisins
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch over double boiler.
Add raisins or nuts.
Drop on waxed paper to cool.

title: chana dal
directions: Chana dal is hulled and split dried chickpeas, one of the many types of legumes available in Indian grocery stores.

title: pecan thins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well. Add flour and salt and mix until smooth.
Stir in chopped pecans and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons, about 2 inches apart, on greased cookie sheet.
Place a pecan half in the center of each cookie. Bake at 375° about 8 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: ham and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower using package directions; drain.
Place in buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with ham.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually. Cook over low heat until thickened and smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour over ham and cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden. Yield: 3 to 4 servings.

title: aunt sara's apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples
and
place
in
a
heavy
covered saucepan, adding only enough
water
to
steam
apples a tender crisp (2 tablespoons will
be enough).
Add lemon juice.
Watch carefully, do not overcook.
Add sugar to which salt and spices have been blended.
Add margarine, stir lightly to blend.
Beat eggs until foamy, add to
apple
mixture lightly and quickly to distribute
eggs without uneven
cooking
of
eggs.
Pour
into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° until well done, about 50 to 60 minutes.
This pie has a partially caramelized topping which is very good.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: green jello salad
directions: Combine lime jello and lemon jello; add hot water and mayonnaise.
Stir until dissolved.
Let set, then add cold water and stir.
Set in refrigerator for 15 minutes, then beat.
Add crushed pineapple with juice, cottage cheese and chopped nuts. Pour in mold and refrigerate.

title: double chocolate crumble bars
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients like a cake.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread marshmallows over it.
Cool. Melt chocolate and peanut butter.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Spread on top the marshmallows.
Chill and cut in bars.

title: frozen pineapple tapioca pudding
directions: Put milk in double boiler.
When boiling, add tapioca; cook clear.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Blend in salt and sugar; cook 2 minutes longer.
Cool; add pineapple, whipped cream, egg whites and blend.
Freeze, or use chilled in refrigerator.

title: special recipe cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage by hand or in a food processor. Peel garlic cloves. Place in blender with water and puree. Combine garlic water with both oils, both vinegars and mayonnaise. Stir to mix and season to taste with salt. Pour over shredded cabbage. Combine well and chill before serving. Serves 8.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into strips.
In large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add onions; cook until limp.
Stir in gravy, wine and tomato paste; season with salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 10 to 20 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Remove from heat; let stand 10 minutes.
Slowly stir in sour cream.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apples, spice and nice brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in one bowl.
Batter will be stiff. Spread in two 8-inch pans or one 8 x 12-inch pan.
Grease pans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream
margarine, oil, powdered sugar, granulated sugar and eggs, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate a
few hours.
Roll
into balls, then in sugar and press with glass. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill at least 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Now mix in margarine, liquid shortening, powdered sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla extract.
Roll into balls, dip into sugar and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: poor man's seafood primavera
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, heat milk, bouillon and both packages of frozen vegetables and pasta in Parmesan sauce to boiling; stirring frequently.
In cup, mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Stir cornstarch mixture into vegetable mixture; heat to boiling; boil 1 minute.
Stir in imitation crabmeat and Parmesan cheese.
Makes six servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook the vegetables with salt, sugar and butter until tender. Mix the soup, mayonnaise and onion with vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: stir-fried green beans
directions: Heat skillet or wok on medium high heat until a drop of water sizzles when sprinkled on it.
Add oil and rotate in skillet to coat bottom.
Add washed beans (ends trimmed) and stir or shake in pan until beans are well coated with oil and begin to char. Sprinkle on soy sauce, stir, then add water and cover.
Simmer on low heat until crispy-tender, approximately 5 to 8 minutes.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix together the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add oatmeal, baking powder, salt and milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with warm milk.

title: merry mix-ups
directions: Mix.
Then put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate chips.
Drizzle condensed milk over mixture evenly. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: molasses-pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed of an electric mixer until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar and next 4 ingredients; beat until blended.
Stir in chopped pecans. Pour mixture into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Garnish with whipped cream and a pecan half, if desired.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until well mixed.
In a large casserole dish, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: alpine appetizer
directions: Combine cheeses, bacon and onion.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add to cheese mixture and mix lightly.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Test for doneness by inserting silver knife which should come out clean.
Cut into squares to fit on stone ground crackers.

title: snow peas oriental
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add oil; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add snow peas and carrots.
Saute 2 minutes.
Add water chestnuts and broth and bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Combine soy sauce and cornstarch, stirring until cornstarch dissolves.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Serves 4. Serve immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain well.
Mix all ingredients except butter.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tamari almonds
directions: Spread almonds on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 20 min., or until nut is browning on the inside.
Sprinkle with soy sauce. They will sizzle.
Keep mixing until the sauce is absorbed.

title: bacon delight sandwiches
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Spread mixture on bread.
Trim crust, if desired. Cut in fourths diagonally.

title: plantation chicken
directions: Cook celery in salted water.
Saute in oleo, the peppers and onion.
Combine flour, broth and soup.
Then add celery, pepper, onion, chicken and heat well.
Salt to taste and cook until broth thickens.
Black pepper may be added.
Line 2 large Pyrex dishes with noodles, then pour in chicken mixture.
Take cheese and bread grated together and sprinkle over all.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach; mix soup and sour cream and blend.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini provencal
directions: Saute onion in oil in a skillet until tender.
Stir in zucchini, tomatoes, green pepper, garlic and seasonings.
Cover and cook over medium heat 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Transfer vegetables to a serving dish and sprinkle with cheese and parsley, if desired.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: egg drops for soup
directions: Beat the eggs; add water, salt and flour.
Mix until smooth. Put on a plate, using a teaspoon scrape a little at a time into boiling salted water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Drain in colander and rinse with cold water.

title: john grover soup(a recipe from sante fe)
directions: In a pot, cover chicken in water and cook until tender. Remove chicken from water and bone and chop.
Cool broth and remove fat.
To broth add onion and garlic.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Add chicken and green chilies; cook 1 more hour.
Add 2 cups cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Mix and heat for 10 minutes.
Add grated Jack cheese and allow to melt.
Serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place whole, cut up chicken on top of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and eggs.
Dice both potatoes and eggs.
Add a jar of Bac*Os and mayonnaise to your liking.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: o susannah pie
directions: Toast pecans and coconut until golden brown; let cool.
Mix cream cheese and milk together and then fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in prepared pie shells 2 layers of cream cheese mixture, pecans and coconut.
Drizzle caramel topping over pecans.
Layer again.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple chunks; reserve 1 1/3 cups of liquid.
Cook pudding and reserved liquid until very thick.
Cool thoroughly!
Add drained fruit and bananas.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jello mandarin orange salad
directions: Whip cottage cheese in food processor or blender until smooth. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add ice cubes to hot Jell-O mixture. Stir until ice cubes melt and mixture begins to thicken and softly set. Immediately fold in whipped cottage cheese, Cool Whip and mandarin oranges. Pour into bowl; cover and chill until salad is completely set.

title: russian tea
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake until mixed.
Use 1 or 2 teaspoons per mug of hot water.

title: cool whip jello cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions.
Let cool slightly.
Mix up jello as package directs.
Poke holes in the cake with a fork.
Pour jello mixture evenly over the cake.
Place in refrigerator and chill 2 hours or overnight.
Spread Cool Whip over top of cake evenly.
Cut and serve.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, then nutmeats and chocolate.
Pour into greased pan, about 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 3/4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When almost cool, cut into squares, about 2 x 2-inch.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Line pan with uncooked beef.
Sprinkle onion on meat.
Add condensed chicken soup on top of onion.
Spread Tater Tots on top of soup.
Mix remaining can of soup and water together and pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave quick lasagna
directions: Crumble ground meat in colander over mixing bowl and microwave on High 5 minutes, stirring halfway.
Discard drippings.
Combine meat, sauce, water and Italian seasonings; set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, egg, parsley, pepper and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese in separate bowl.
Pour 1/4-inch meat sauce in baking dish.
Layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese mixture, then Mozzarella cheese. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 8 minutes.
Simmer (1/3 power) for 20 minutes; sprinkle on remaining Parmesan cheese. Allow to stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: lemon ice box cake
directions: Mix the two well and let stand. (Reserve 1 cup of milk and lemon juice mixture.) When cake has completely cooled ice the top of each cake layer with rest of mixture. Mix 8 oz. cool whip with the reserved mixture and ice sides and top of cake.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain off fat after browned.
Add onion, saute until limp, stirring occasionally.
Mix taco sauce, green chilies, mushroom soup and enchilada sauce.
In a large casserole, layer meat mixture, Doritos, soup mixture, beans and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chewy popcorn balls(kids cooking)
directions: Grown Ups:
Pop popcorn.
Turn stove on and supervise cooking.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; chop apples with peelings.
Peel and chunk oranges.
Stir together with pecans.
Add sugar and allow to set until sugar is dissolved.
Mix Jell-O and hot water and add to fruit mixture; chill until set.

title: stuffed cube steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make stuffing according to package instructions.
Roll inside cubed steak.
Place in ovenproof casserole.
Pour gravy over top.
Cover and cook for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal chocolate chips(big recipe)
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream eggs and sugar. Add milk and vanilla.
Add flour.
Mix until all is well mixed and add oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour; mix.
Add milk.
Chip the cheese you desire in the mixture (I prefer Velveeta cheese).
Cook slowly until smooth and thick.
This comes out good in microwave.
Add Worcestershire sauce, garlic and pepper.

title: oven baked parmesan chicken
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Pat dry chicken parts with paper towel.
Dust chicken with flour.
Roll in egg and milk mixture. Shake in coating.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend on low and pour into graham cracker crust. Makes 2 pies. Freeze.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend shortening into flour and salt.
Sprinkle on the vinegar.
Add milk (slowly you may not need it all) and mix until dough holds together.
Roll lightly to desired size.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Store in dry place.
Serve 2 tablespoons in cup of hot water.

title: breakfast surprise pie
directions: Line pie crust with cheese; top with sausage.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; heat. Pour over sausage in shells.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°. Serve hot out of oven.

title: sherrille's banana cream pizza
directions: Press biscuits together and roll into a 13 inch circle. Place on a 12 inch pizza pan, sprayed with a non-stick cooking spray. Turn up edges of dough to form a ridge. Let rise 10 minutes. Combine brown sugar, butter and pecans. Sprinkle evenly over crust. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool crust completely. Arrange bananas on crust. Spoon prepared pudding over bananas. Top with whipped topping.

title: creamy pudding frosting
directions: Mix pudding and milk until well blended.
Next fold in Cool Whip.
Stir until smooth and well blended.

title: beefy barbecue beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add beans and barbecue sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until thickened.
Serve as main dish on hamburger buns or over corn bread.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix
pudding with milk according to package directions. Add sour cream and Cool Whip to pudding mixture.

title: scottish crofter's pie
directions: Roll your pie crust 1/8-inch thicker than a normal pie crust.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Let sit for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice; mix well.
Divide coconut and pecans into tart shells.
Pour egg mixture over tart shells.
Place on cookie sheets to bake.
Don't overfill.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy mexican dip
directions: Place cream cheese and chili in a microwave-safe dish. Microwave on High until cream cheese has softened.
Mix until completely blended.
Continue to microwave until hot.
Serve with Mexican chips.

title: downhome punch
directions: Mix all together; stir.
Garnish with orange and cherry and party.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix well. Can also be frozen.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Put
oil in a cast iron skillet and place in oven to get hot while you mix everything together
Sift all dry ingredients together, stir to make sure they are completely blended.
Add
milk and egg and stir just until everything is blended.
Stir in some of the hot oil
just until blended, do not over stir.
Pour into hot skillet.
Bake for 20
minutes or until golden brown.

title: holiday nectar
directions: Combine pineapple concentrate, orange concentrate and pear nectar in a punch bowl.
Slowly add 7-Up.
Makes about 12 (6 oz.) servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan and saute onion until clear. Add chicken broth.
Mix flour with 1/2 cup half and half.
Add slowly to broth mixture.
Cook until desired thickness.
Add broccoli and remaining half and half and heat through.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: lentil cheese loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 1 pound loaf tin.
Wash lentils twice in cold water and drain well.
Cover in saucepan with twice their volume of water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer lentils for 20 minutes (until soft).
Mix in cheese, onion, salt, pepper and herbs.
Add bread crumbs, egg and butter to lentil mixture.
Stir well.
(Add more bread crumbs if mixture is sloppy.)
Press into tin and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn over onto platter and serve hot.
Good source of protein and calcium.

title: lemon butter
directions: Beat or use blender to mix and cook over medium heat, stirring often until thick (as you would pudding).
This will thicken when cold.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetables or spread on bread.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, tomato soup and vinegar. Pour over carrot mixture and mix. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: mint julep
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes, without stirring. Let cool. Pour over loosely filled quart jar of uncrushed mint. Cap and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours. Make 1 julep at a time by filling a chilled julep glass with finely crushed ice. Pour in 1/2 tablespoon mint flavoring syrup and add 2 ounces bourbon.

title: almond sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sour cream.
Sift flour and soda together.
Alternate flour mixture with eggs.
Add flavors.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: festive green been casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute red pepper and onion in butter until tender. Add soup, milk, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce, stir until smooth. Stir in beans and chestnuts. Pour into an ungreased 1- 1/2 qt. baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes or heated through.

title: cranberry drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla, egg and orange peel.
Combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture until just blended.
Fold in nuts and cranberries. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: earthquake cake
directions: For first layer, put nuts in pan; for second layer, put in coconut.
Mix cake mix according to directions and put in pan as third layer.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil fryer until done; debone.
Cook spaghetti.
Add chicken, mushroom soup, pimentos, bell pepper and onion.
Stir together. In a separate saucepan, cook cheese and Ro-Tel until melted.
Add spaghetti and stir.
Add chicken broth to blend.
Cook 30 minutes or until onion is done.
This can be frozen and is very good later.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: italian pepper steak
directions: Combine oil, green peppers and onions in 10 x 6 x 2-inch oblong baking dish.
Microwave, uncovered, at time cook (level 10), saute until vegetables are soft, stirring twice.
Add steak and seasonings.
Microwave uncovered at time cook (Low) for 8 to 9 minutes or until beef is cooked, stirring twice.
Serve over rice or in hero rolls.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar with a spoon; add eggs, then food coloring and water, then cocoa. Blend in buttermilk; add flour and salt gradually. Add vanilla and beat well with spoon. Mix vinegar and soda together and fold into mixture. Do not beat. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven. Makes 2 (9-inch) layers or 9 x 13-inch sheet cake. Frost with Fluff Frosting.

title: three week slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, green pepper, onions and sugar together; let stand while you prepare the rest.

title: nut rolls
directions: Combine dry yeast and water in small bowl.
In another bowl, blend butter (margarine) and flour as in pie dough.
Add eggs, milk and sugar to the middle of the dough mixture.
Add yeast mixture and blend.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Separate dough into three or four portions.
Roll in circle very thin. Spread with butter (not too much or it will run out and burn), brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up as for jelly roll and place on cookie sheet forming a ring.
Cut to 1/2 inch from bottom in 1 1/2 inch wide pieces.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost top, if desired.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Serve as a slush.

title: hilda's pink stuff
directions: Mix Jell-O with Cool Whip.
Add cottage cheese and crushed pineapple.
(Add walnuts.)
Leave overnight in Frigadaire.

title: sweet cinnamon quick bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, and
vanilla. Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.

title: brigadeiros(dessert)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes loose from the sides of the pan when pan is turned sideways.
Pour into a buttered Pyrex dish.
Let cool completely.
Shape into small balls and roll in chocolate sprinkles or colored sugar.
Place in small candy cups available at craft stores.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: In a quart baking dish with tight lid, layer rice, corn, salt and pepper.
Pour one can tomato sauce and 4 ounces water over rice and corn.
Add chopped onions and green pepper.
Add uncooked ground beef.
Salt and pepper.
Pour can of tomato sauce and 4 ounces water over top.
Cover meat with bacon strips.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer until brown and crisp.

title: spam casserole
directions: Place seashells and peas in casserole dish.
Then place Spam and cheese next.
Add the soup; stir the mixture and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Dilute mushroom soup with milk.
Place cracker crumbs and dots of butter into bottom of casserole dish. Add a layer of asparagus, sprinkled with onions.
Cover this with mushroom soup.
Repeat layers until you use all ingredients. Sprinkle the top with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon in small bowl. Roll bread dough into balls; dip into butter, then roll in sugar mixture. Put into a cake pan. Sprinkle with nuts (optional). Pour left over butter and sugar over the top. Let raise again. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together.
Add remaining ingredients together; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, egg, honey and lemon juice together. Add remaining ingredients.
After all is combined, chill dough. Roll out 1/4-inch thick and use cookie cutters.
Grease baking sheet and preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Season chicken breasts with Nature's Seasons blend.
Beat together egg and milk; dip chicken breasts in egg and milk, then dip into fine bread crumbs.
Brown on both sides in butter or oleo. Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour the following over chicken:
1 cup chicken stock and 1 small can mushrooms.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons dry onion soup mix over all.
Stir in.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: winter party salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: hot bean dish
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef, bacon and onion.
Drain off excess fat.
To beef mixture, add beans, ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake, covered, for 1 hour in a 325° oven.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: syrian cheese
directions: Makes about 4 patties.

title: taco casserole
directions: Lay crescent rolls in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown hamburger and drain, then add 1/2 cup water with the taco seasoning and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and mix well. Put a layer of chips over crust, then hamburger, then another layer of chips.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake 10 to 15 minutes until crust is done. Put shredded lettuce, tomatoes and olives on top to serve.

title: corn and crab appetizer
directions: Combine corn, red pepper, onion, garlic and butter. Cover loosely with wax paper. Microwave on High for 4 minutes or until hot, stirring halfway through cooking. Stir in cayenne pepper, sour cream and crab meat. Cover and microwave on High for 30 seconds or until warm. Do not boil.

title: reuben bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat baking sheet with cooking spray.
Place rye bread on baking sheet.
Coat each piece of bread with cooking spray.
Spread 1/2 tsp. dressing on each piece of bread.
Layer each with a piece of Swiss cheese and corned beef and 2 tsp. sauerkraut.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Yields 24 small Reubens.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook 1 cup berries with sugar, cornstarch and water until thick and transparent.
Add cinnamon to mixture, if desired, after removing from stove.
Cool a bit; add remaining raw berries.
Put in pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: rhubarb dumplings
directions: Mix 2 cups sugar and cinnamon.
Prepare a batter of flour, salt and enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Take 1/6 of dough; roll out.
Put 1/2 cup rhubarb on dough.
Put 3 tablespoons of sugar mixture on top of rhubarb.
Add 1 tablespoon butter; pinch together at top.
Repeat with the rest of dough.
Place in deep oven dish. Pour a syrup made of brown sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian pineapple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Stir baking mix, flour and soda together. Beat sugar, sour cream, butter and vanilla together for 2 minutes. Add eggs and beat 1 minute. Add flour mixture and beat 1 minute longer. Mix in drained pineapple and rum and pour into a well-greased 9-inch Bundt pan. Bake for about 45 minutes or until tests done. Remove from oven and spoon half the glaze over cake. Let stand 10 minutes. Turn out onto serving plate and spoon remaining glaze over cake. Cool before cutting.

title: waffles
directions: Preheat waffle machine.
In large bowl with wire whisk, mix first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
When waffle maker is ready, pour batter over (it takes about 1 cup of batter).
Cook until done, about 4 to 5 minutes until nicely brown.
Makes 4 cups of batter.

title: yogurt cheesecake
directions: To yogurt, add sugar, egg yolks, flour, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into yogurt mixture. Pour mixture into graham cracker crust; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone.
Melt 1 stick of butter. Crumble 1 to 2 sleeves of Ritz crackers into butter; mix, then line bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken.
Mix together 2 cans cream of chicken soup, sour cream and broth from boiled chicken (about 3/4 cup or enough to make mixture thin enough to pour over chicken).
Melt the other stick of butter and crumble into it 2 sleeves of Ritz crackers (crushed).
Layer across top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes, or until brown on top and soup bubbles.

title: harvest apple pie
directions: In small bowl, combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup flour and vanilla.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in walnuts; reserve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, olives, onions and 3/4 cup pecans. Save remainder of pecans to roll cheese ball in.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoon in hot broth, not boiling. Cover and cook 12 to 15 minutes until not doughy on bottom.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In a small skillet over medium-high heat, melt margarine.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper; saute 3 minutes.
Set aside.
Place broth and rice in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion mixture and mushrooms.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 30 to 40 minutes, or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Add parsley and black pepper.
Fluff before serving.
Note:
This dish may be made ahead and reheated.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Mix ingredients (except venison); bring to a boil. Stir occasionally while simmering for 10 minutes. Pour over venison that has been sauteed in hot fat to brown. Roast in 350° oven for about 1 to 2 hours. It would pay to turn occasionally.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Brown wieners in 1 Tbsp. oil.
Put in baking dish.
Brown peppers and onions in 1 Tbsp. oleo until tender.
Combine all ingredients except wieners and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over wieners in baking dish and bake in preheated 350 degree oven covered for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large Dutch oven and add water to cover.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and cool, reserving broth for other uses.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together Duncan Hines cake mix as directed on package. Add coconut (approximately 1 1/2 packages).
Put the mixture in three 9-inch cake pans.
Do not overcook.
Cool completely, then ice.

title: scalloped bread with onions
directions: Saute onions.
Add milk flavored with parsley or sage, salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and take top crust that has formed. Break into small pieces.
Add grated cheese and 1 tablespoon melted oleomargarine.
Sprinkle over top.
Return to oven.
Bake until golden brown, about 5 minutes.

title: old-fashioned egg cornbread
directions: Put oil into a 10-inch well-seasoned skillet and preheat at 400° until very hot.
Mix all other ingredients together and when oil is hot, pour about half into mixture and stir.
Then pour batter into the pan with the hot oil; do not stir now.
This will make a nice crust and should keep bread from sticking.
Bake 35 minutes at 400° or until top is brown.
Take from oven and turn onto a plate immediately.
Serve while hot.
Recipe can be cut in half except for oil and using same 10-inch skillet.
Will make a nice, thin, crusty bread.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: With a small sharp knife, cut 1/2-inch deep slits about 1 inch apart in chicken.
Put chicken in a 1-gallon size food storage bag or large bowl.
Add lemon juice; toss chicken to coat with juice. Mix yogurt, ginger root, paprika, garlic, coriander, cumin and ground red pepper in a small bowl.
Pour into bag or bowl with chicken.
Close bag and turn to coat chicken, rubbing marinade into slits, or use your hands to coat chicken.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours, but preferably overnight.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Mix spinach, Ricotta and seasoning salt.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture.
Put a layer of spaghetti sauce in baking pan. Place stuffed shells on sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over top. Put Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together until onion is tender. Drain fat.
Add other ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Stuff peppers lightly.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover
and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: almond bark bars
directions: Pour melted bark and peanut butter over dry ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cool 20 minutes and cut. If cooled too long, it will be hard to cut.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Take half of the strawberries and crush them.
Stir in cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook the strawberries and cornstarch mixture in a pan until liquid becomes clear and thick. Let mixture cool.
Cut rest of the berries in half and fold into the cold berries.
Fill crust and refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Put cherry pie filling in 9 x 13-inch oblong cake pan.
Add crushed pineapple over top.
Add dry cake mix; spread over the top of the fruit filling.
Melt butter and drizzle over cake mix.
Add chopped nuts and coconut, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Allow to cool.

title: no bake date roll
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan.
Add dates to butter, then add sugar.
Cook for 5 minutes, then add remaining ingredients.
Put on powdered sugar waxed paper.
Roll into long loaf.
Cool.
Slice thin.

title: pay day candy
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and Karo syrup to a rolling boil. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter.
Mix together.
Pour over peanuts and Rice Chex, then mix all together.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Cut into squares, then pig out.

title: sweet and salty party mix
directions: Place cereals, pretzels and nuts in a baking dish.
Melt oleo and stir in salts; pour over cereal mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook, uncovered, in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Bring to a rapid boil the next 4 ingredients and pour over first mixture. Stir soda, buttermilk and eggs well; beat together and add to mixture.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and noodle casserole #2
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove all skin from chicken and discard.
Remove all chicken from bones.
Set chicken aside. Bring the broth from the chicken to a boil and add the noodles. Cook noodles until tender.
Add all other ingredients except bread crumbs and canned chicken broth.
Use broth only if needed for extra moisture.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch lightly greased pan.

title: orange-honey glazed chicken
directions: Coat chicken with bread crumbs.
In large skillet, heat oil; brown chicken on both sides.
In small bowl, blend remaining ingredients, except onion.
Pour over chicken.
Add sliced onion. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Baste with sauce occasionally.

title: low-fat jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese into batter.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased 10-inch heavy skillet.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over batter.
Pour in remaining batter and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake in 425° oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: smoked sausage in sauce
directions: Cook sausage.
Drain and add to sauce mixture.
Best served when hot and can be kept hot in a crock-pot.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Melt margarine and soak chicken for 5 minutes. Roll (or shake in bag) each piece of chicken into bread crumb mixture. Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish and let stand in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Serves 10.
(Recipe can be cut in half.)

title: chicken pesto pasta
directions: Mix and cook together.
It's better if made the night before.

title: sangria
directions: Combine in a pitcher and serve in glasses over crushed ice.

title: honey apple peanut butter spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl; mix well.
Serve as spread for	sandwiches, toast, crackers, rice cakes, bagels or flour tortillas.
Use as a dip for fresh fruit slices, such as apples, pears or
oranges.	Makes
about
2 1/2 cups.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening together.
Add yolk to cup and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Mix well.

title: egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured 9-inch pie plate. Bake for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients, except shrimp.
Add shrimp. Bring to boil again.
Stir, reduce heat.
Boil slowly for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Combine soup mix with bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in bread crumb mixture, coating well.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Toss cheeses together.
Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients except Doritos chips and cheese.
Layer in order 1/2 Doritos chips, 1/2 meat sauce and 1/2 cheeses; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or microwave for about 15 minutes.

title: shrimp seafood pasta salad
directions: Cut up crab meat while it is still frozen into pieces.
Cook shrimp in salted water per package directions and cool.
Add crab meat to shrimp.
Cook pasta al dente; drain in cold water.
Cut up celery and onions and add to seafood and pasta mixture.
Add Miracle Whip or whatever dressing you prefer.
Add spices to taste.

title: waldorf salad mold
directions: Combine apples, celery and marshmallows.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in remaining 3/4 cup of water, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until syrupy.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and oleo.
Beat in eggs, oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press down with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 375° until lightly brown on edge.

title: soybean waffles
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Add oats.
Bake on waffle iron!

title: cherry bonbons
directions: Melt margarine in a two-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in milk, vanilla and salt.
Gradually add sugar.
Turn onto a board sprinkled with additional powdered sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Add nuts and cherries.
Shape into a roll; wrap in waxed paper and chill until firm.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.

title: orange soaked angel cake
directions: Place cake on serving platter.
Using meat fork, pierce top of cake at 1-inch intervals.
Set aside.
Combine fruits and set aside.
Combine last 3 ingredients.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir.
Toss fruit with syrup.
Spoon fruit over cake, allowing syrup to soak into cake.
Cover and chill before serving. Makes 12 servings.
One serving:
229 calories, no fat, no cholesterol and 346 mg of sodium.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle seasoned salt over pecans.
Stir well.
Pour on cookie sheet and bake at 325° about 30 minutes or until toasted.
Stir often while baking.

title: margaret's blueberry cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon in one bowl.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add blueberries last.
Before putting in oven, sprinkle generously with white sugar.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°. Delicious served warm.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, add sugar, condensed milk and lemon juice. Pour filling into pie crust.
Add meringue and bake at 400° until brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake in sheet cake pan.
Cook sugar and milk until thickens, then add one small package coconut.
Pour over warm cake and let cool.

title: velveeta cheese dip
directions: Heat until all cheese is melted and all ingredients are blended.
Put in crock-pot to keep warm.
Soo good!
Dip with corn chips.
(Half of recipe fills my small crock-pot.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Place in a dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs (Ritz or Bacon Thins).
Dot with butter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ground beef soup
directions: Put salt and pepper into meat; form into medium sized balls. Drop into rapidly boiling salt water.
Add all the vegetables in order given.
Lastly, drop in bouillon.
Cover and reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with Italian bread.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes in flat bake pan, then layer of zucchini, layer of meat and the cheese.
Pour soup over top and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
This is a one dish meal for 2 to 4. Delicious with fresh bread.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with fork.
In separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the two; keep stirring with fork until the ingredients are moistened.
Mold the dough with hands. Chill for at least 20 minutes before using.
Dough can be kept in refrigerator until used up.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Looks pretty in glass.
Cool.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping as directed on package; use 1 cup milk.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and pudding mix.
Using a mixer, beat at high speed for 2 minutes or until thick.
Spoon into pie shell and chill at least 4 hours.

title: hot dried beef dip
directions: Add milk to softened cream cheese.
Snip beef with kitchen shears.
Add seasoning and blend well.
Place in pie plate.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbling. Serve with crackers or Fritos.
May also be served uncooked as a cold dip.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add liquid and mix again.
Stir in nuts, coconut, etc.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Marinate pork in Allegro overnight.
Pat with cornstarch. Place in open pan and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk. Boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Stir well. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. Let set about 20 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: low-fat strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzel sticks, 4 tablespoons of sugar and melted butter; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: cola chicken
directions: Put chicken in nonstick skillet.
Pour catsup and diet cola over the top.
Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and cook for 45 minutes.
Uncover, turn up the heat and continue to cook until the sauce becomes thick and adheres to the chicken.
It turns into the most incredible barbecue sauce.
Yummm!

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat oleo and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: big joe's fish fry
directions: Marinate fish in milk, hot sauce and mustard mixture for at least 1 hour.
Heat oil to 325°.
Dredge fish in fish fry to coat just prior to frying.
Don't get in a hurry; fry just enough fish so the temperature does not decrease by more than 30°.
Fry until golden brown and fish is beginning to float.
Drain and transfer to paper towel.
Salt to taste.
Serve hot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend well and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: caramelized pearl onions with brussels sprouts
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat. Add onions; cook 1 minute. Drain; cool slightly. Add Brussels sprouts to boiling water. Cook until tender, 15 to 20 minutes; drain and set aside.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut stew meat in small bite size pieces.
Brown the meat in large frying pan with 1/2 cup olive or corn oil.
Cut up potatoes in quarter sizes and slice carrots in bite size pieces.
After meat is browned, add 1/2 cup flour to meat (still in pan) and work in with grease.
Add 1/2 to 1 pint cold water to make gravy. (Salt and pepper to taste.)
Put all (meat and gravy, carrots and potatoes) into Dutch oven with a whole onion.
Bake at 350° for an hour or 3 to 4 hours on low in a crock-pot.
Serve with biscuits.

title: cosmopolitan chicken
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place deboned chicken breast in mixture (coating both sides), then dip in Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix.
Place in baking dish.
Pour 1 stick melted margarine over chicken.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cook covered for 1/2 the time.

title: charlotte beau rivage
directions: Use a 10-inch spring-form pan for a flatter cake, or use a smaller spring-form pan for higher slices.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add enough dressing to coat.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for nuts. Form a ball with the mixture. Pour nuts on a piece of aluminum foil and roll ball to cover completely. Serve with Ritz Crackers.

title: brickle crunch candy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Lay out crackers on cookie sheet, packing tightly.

In a medium sized saucepan, melt butter, add sugar and boil, stirring frequently for 2 to 3 minutes until sugar is completely dissolved. Immediately pour mixture over crackers and bake 7 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate and peanut butter morsels over crackers, spreading evenly as they melt.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Break into pieces.
Store in refrigerator. Also great with chopped nuts or coconut.
(Better than Fannie Farmers crunch.)

title: aunt bert's homemade ice cream(1 gallon)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into freezer container.
Add milk to 3-inches from top.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Parboil until skins burst.
Put all ingredients in pot and just barely cover with hot water.

title: mashed potato fudge
directions: Melt the chocolate in a double boiler.
In a large bowl, put the butter, vanilla and mashed potatoes and stir well.
Add the coconut, reserving some for topping, if desired.
Add the confectioners sugar, 1 bag (or box) at a time, mixing well between each, until the mixture is thick.
On a cookie sheet place wax paper and butter.

Then spread the mixture onto the buttered wax paper and spread with half the melted chocolate and allow to dry. Turn over carefully onto a board and peel off the waxed paper. Spread the rest of the melted chocolate evenly over the fudge and sprinkle the coconut over it.
Let dry and cut into small pieces.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour, then nuts.
Spread very flat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes or until crust is brown.
Take from oven and crumble into crumbs.
Reserve 3/4 cup of crumbs for topping.
Press remainder of crumbs in bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Let cool and fill with softened ice cream.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup topping crumbs over pie.
Freeze and serve frozen with Chocolate Sauce (recipe follows).

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place cheese and pepperoni on bottom of an 8-inch pie plate.
Set aside.
In a bowl mix eggs, milk and basil.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.
(Replace milk with 1/2% to 1% milk, eggs with Second Nature No Cholesterol Egg Product and cheese with Kraft No Fat cheese for low fat, low cholesterol version.)

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Add eggs.
Add jam.
Add flour and spice alternately with buttermilk and soda mixture.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Once baked, keeps several weeks.

title: pizza meltaways
directions: Cut French bread lengthwise.
Spread sauce on bread.
Sprinkle cheeses and oregano over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Serves 3 to 4.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender for 1 minute.
Pour into greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain first 4 ingredients.
Mix together all ingredients, except onion rings.
Put into a large pan or casserole dish and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Arrange onion rings on top and return to oven until heated (about 5 minutes).

title: cody's scrabble mix
directions: Mix cereal and nuts in big roaster pan.
Put in 250° oven to heat slightly.
Add butter, salt, Worcestershire and Tabasco. Stir occasionally.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of mixture and bake 10 minutes more.

title: martha's sweet potatoes and praline topping
directions: Drain and mash sweet potatoes.
Add all other ingredients to potatoes, mixing well after each addition.
Place in shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Praline Topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: linguine with clam sauce-white(linguine con vongole bianco)
directions: In medium saucepan
heat
oil
and
saute
garlic until golden brown.
Remove
from
oil and discard.
Remove oil from heat while you
prepare
clams.
Strain
juice through several layers of cheese cloth
and
set
aside.
Wash and chop clams; set aside. Heat oil
and
pour clam juice into oil.
Bring to boil and add red pepper, parsley, wine (optional) and pepper. Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add
clams
and bring back to boil. Cover and remove from
heat.
Let sit until linguine is cooked according to package
directions.
Cook
linguine
in
salted water and when cooked "al dente", drain.
Pour clam sauce over linguine
and serve
immediately.
Sprinkle
with
additional parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes until tender in large skillet.

title: grilled cheese sandwich pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine egg, flour, salt, pepper and half of milk.
Using a rotary beater, beat until smooth.
Add remaining milk; beat until well blended.
Stir in one-half of cheese.
Pour into a well-greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and bake just until cheese is melted, about 2 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Put all dry ingredients together; add corn.
Then add egg yolks (beaten thick), then fold in beaten egg whites.
Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls and fry in hot grease.

title: codfish cakes
directions: Soak codfish in water overnight.
Drain fish, then add more water and boil about 10 minutes.
Drain fish again and press out the excess water.

title: beef-n-cheese tart
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown meat lightly in a skillet.
Add onion and cook 3 minutes.
Drain fat.
Add barbecue sauce and stir.
Prepare pastry.
Roll half into a 15 x 6 1/2-inch rectangle on a lightly floured surface.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Spread meat mixture along center of pastry, leaving a 1-inch border at edges.
Place cheese slices, slightly overlapping on meat. Moisten pastry edge with water.
Roll out remaining pastry. Carefully place pastry over meat/cheese filling, matching edges of bottom pastry.
Seal edges with fork.
Brush pastry with milk and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Brown together ground beef, onion, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and salt.
Drain off grease, then add tomatoes, chili beans and bell pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 15 minutes.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to directions on box.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed celery snacks
directions: In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, carrot and seasonings. Stuff into celery.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.
Yield: About 2 dozen.

title: cold meat
directions: Cook the meat by boiling in a deep pot, covered with water, and 1 tablespoon each of salt, onions, green peppers and tomato. When meat is soft enough (1 1/2 hours), cut it into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on plate in this order, 1 slice meat, lettuce, tomato, red or green peppers and onions, all sliced.
Prepare a dressing with the vinegar, black pepper and salt.

title: creme de menthe torte
directions: Mix chocolate Oreos and melted butter and reserve 1/3 cup for topping.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Combine marshmallow cream and creme de menthe.
Fold in cream and freeze until served.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: In a skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup and basil; set aside.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Add cinnamon candies to water in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat and stir until candy is dissolved.
Add jello and dissolve.
Add applesauce, salt and nutmeg.
Pour into bowl or 8 x 8-inch pan. Chill until set.

title: potato casserole
directions: Take a cup of love.
Add a dash of care.
Mix with kindness. Add a bit of patience.
Top it off with faith.
Sprinkle liberally with understanding.
Share with everyone you meet throughout the year.

title: wild rice venison casserole
directions: Dredge venison in flour.
Brown in bacon fat with onion.
Add to 3-quart baking pan with next six ingredients.
Parboil wild rice in water.
Boil until almost tender.
Add to baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: penne pasta casserole
directions: Cook beef or turkey until crumbly.
Drain.
Stir in diced tomatoes, sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Season to taste, heat through. Coat a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan with Pam spray.
Combine cooked pasta with meat-tomato mixture and 2 cups mozzarella cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Top evenly with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 350 degree oven for 20 - 25 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: cheese omelet(makes 4 servings)
directions: Melt margarine in hot skillet, turn down heat.
Beat all ingredients together, using 1/4 cup cheese.
Pour egg mixture into skillet.
As edges of omelet begin to thicken, draw cooked portions toward the center to allow uncooked mixture to flow to the bottom of the skillet.
Shake as necessary to aid flow of uncooked eggs. When surface is still moist, but no longer flows, loosen edges carefully and fold in half.
Sprinkle on a little of the remaining cheese and slide onto a plate.

title: pasta with broccoli and chicken
directions: Heat oil over medium heat.
Saute garlic until golden brown. Add chicken strips and saute until white and almost completely cooked (7 to 10 minutes).
Add broccoli and saute until still crisp.
Add tomatoes, basil, red pepper, salt and pepper.
Add wine, chicken broth and butter.
Cook until heated through (5 minutes), stirring frequently.
Toss with fresh cooked bow tie pasta.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: leslie's oreo ice cream pie
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted butter to form crust.
Place in a Pyrex pie dish and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool pie crust and fill with soft ice cream.
Top with swirls of chocolate syrup.
Freeze until ready to use.
Take out of freezer about 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash. Add salad dressing mixture, then fill egg whites with yolk mixture.

title: fruit salad
directions: Break your lettuce up into medium-size pieces; peel tomatoes and dice them in small pieces.
Peel cantaloupe and slice it in long slices; then take each slice at a time and cut into bite-size pieces.
Drain liquid off pineapple.
Put all ingredients in a large mixing bowl, except dressing.
Mix ingredients together and serve in small salad bowls with Ranch dressing to each one's taste.

title: pearl's cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed, adding the pudding, half of the Mandarin oranges and 1/2 of pineapple. Pour into two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans. Bake as directed. When done, cool cakes before icing.

title: florida lobster cocktail
directions: Mix together ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, Key Lime juice, Tabasco sauce and horseradish. Add salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with lemon quarters. May substitute cooked shrimp for lobster.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Dip balls in coating; turn with fork until balls are covered with coating and lay on wax paper to firm up.
Yields approximately 5 dozen and keeps indefinitely.

title: flounder florentine
directions: In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, combine onion and garlic; cover and cook until onion is soft.
Add mushrooms and cook, stirring constantly, until all liquid has evaporated.
Add spinach, salt and pepper and stir to combine.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Spoon 1/2 of spinach mixture onto center of each fillet; roll fillets to enclose filling and place seam side down in shallow, 1-quart casserole.

title: white bread
directions: Add the white sugar, lard and salt to the warm water in a bowl.
Add the white flour (enough to make a paste), then add the yeast, which was dissolved in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough (13 to 14 cups).
Let rise; punch down. Let rise, then put in pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Pour on cooled cake without beating.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening together.
Add egg.
Mix sifted flour, salt and baking powder together.
Boil water; add soda and pour over dates.
Cool.
Add to sugar and shortening.
Add chopped nuts to flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind ham and fresh pork.
Mix all ingredients with enough milk to barely hold shape.
Form into loaf and place in pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Blend the following ingredients and baste after 1/2 hour and then every 15 minutes:

title: bacon cheese fingers
directions: Stir together first five ingredients, spread over bread slices.
Cut each slice into three strips.
Placed on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: straw-berry blend
directions: Blend until thick, but not chunky.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit overnight.
Cut fruit into bite-sized pieces. Grease 9 x 12-inch glass casserole with butter.
Place fruit, mixed, into casserole.
Cover fruit with pie filling, then almonds. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Really good accompaniment with ham, fish or poultry.
Serves 10 or 12.

title: children's lemonade
directions: Squeeze the lemons and put juice
and some remaining chunks in a large bowl.
Put in the water, sugar and a pinch of salt.
Stir well. When the sugar is dissolved, put in some ice cubes and stir to get the lemonade cold.
Pour into individual glasses and let each person enjoy!

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Mix melted butter or margarine, brown sugar and eggs in a large bowl of electric mixer, then add remaining ingredients, mixing all together.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well. Mix in flour and 7-Up in three portions (1 cup flour and 1/4 cup 7-Up).
Mix well after adding each portion.
Add lemon extract. Grease and flour Bundt pan and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: rossi family lasagne
directions: In a large skillet or deep, large pot; saute garlic and onion in olive oil until caramelized, starting with onion first and adding garlic when onion softens and looks transparent, so garlic doesn't burn.
Add large can or 2 of tomatoes, paste, Italian spices and bay leaf, cooking on low heat until thickened, usually an hour or more.
In separate pan, brown Italian sausage with ground beef.
Drain and add to marinara sauce, along with pepperoni, if desired.

Meanwhile, cook noodles, adding bouillon, basil and olive oil to salted water; cooking until al dente, draining, but not rinsing and set aside on wax paper until needed. In large mixing bowl, mix all cheese together with 10 to 12 eggs along with drained spinach and gently mixing until well combined. Remove marinara, meat sauce from heat.
Lightly grease a deep, oblong pan with olive oil.
Begin layering sauce, noodles, then egg and cheese mixtures in pan, starting with marinara sauce, then noodles, egg mixture, repeating until all is used.
Top with grated Mozzarella and bake at 350° for at least 45 minutes (no more than 1 hour) to thoroughly heat and top begins to brown lightly.
Freezes well.
Makes 2 to 3 pans.

title: egg and tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: bacon crunchy chip dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add catsup, mustard, ginger and sour cream.
Blend well.
Serve with potato chips or crackers.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Heat oven according to directions on biscuit can.
Brown meat and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain thoroughly.
Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar; simmer.
Spray muffin tins lightly with Pam.
Flatten biscuits between fingers until large enough to make a cup in the muffin tin.
Stuff with meat; top with cheese. Bake at 400° until edges of biscuits are lightly browned.
Remove immediately.

title: zucchini crumb quiche
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie pan and line with bread crumbs.
Cut zucchini into thin slices.
Allow to drain on paper towels. Saute squash in olive oil.
Drain again on paper towels.
Melt margarine; add flour.
Add scalded milk, stirring until thickened. Stir in cheese, egg and seasonings.
Add zucchini and ladle into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole, top with potato chips, if desired.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: In mixing bowl, combine egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
In small saucepan, melt butter; add seasoned stuffing mix, tossing to coat.
Stir 3/4 of the mixture into vegetable mixture.
