Turn into an ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle the 1/4 mix over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve hot.

title: italian sausage stir-fry
directions: Combine and cook until done.
And you can fix cooked pasta and put vegetables over the top of them for a meal.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Cream butter and 1 box of sugar.
Add liquids, then coconut. Add second box of sugar and mix well.
Roll into small balls and roll into ground cinnamon.
Chill.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together and bake according to cake mix box directions.

title: posh squash
directions: Cook squash in boiling salted water to cover for 10 - 15 mins. or until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Combine mayo, cheese, onion, eggs, salt and pepper:
stir until well combined. Add squash, stir.
Pour squash mixture in greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Spoon over squash.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 mins.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine in electric blender.
Cover and blend 3 minutes on low speed.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for forty minutes. Can add coconut or 4 tablespoons cocoa, 1/4 cup sugar and a little margarine.

title: pink velvet salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into pan and freeze.

title: "the dish"
directions: Saute meat in a small amount of vegetable oil.
Add onions and pepper and cook until they are almost done.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese.
Cook the mixture for 45 minutes.

title: ricy spicy meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add ground beef, mixing well.
Shape into balls.
Cook for 15 minutes at 400° or until well browned. Drain well.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Put prepared turnips in a pot with water to cover and the salt.
Cook until well done, about 1 hour.
Drain.
Mash; add milk, sugar and butter and continue mixing.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: special hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Pour into greased baking dish; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; uncover.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix boiling water and jello.
Let cool, but not set.
Add the other ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until center is completely set, about 35 minutes.

title: spanish paella
directions: Cook rice according to pkg.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute onions and peppers.
Add chicken and continue to saute until chicken is partially cooked.
Stir in remaining ingredients except tomatoes and garlic.
Cover and steam until the chicken and shrimp are fully cooked.
Stir in tomatoes and garlic.
Add cooked rice. 4 servings.

title: creamy lemon pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple (save).
Mix cheese, pineapple, celery, nut meats and salt.
Heat juice and mix in Jell-O.
Add to cheese mixture.
Whip the cream and fold into cheese mixture. Pour into low baking dish.
Chill.
Cut into squares and serve on bed of lettuce.

title: old-fashioned candy
directions: Combine ingredients and knead until mixture can be rolled out. Form into balls and dip in melted chocolate.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into electric freezer can. Freeze as usual.

title: tomato relish
directions: Chop green tomatoes; add salt.
Allow to stand overnight; drain.
Chop ripe tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Add green tomatoes.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 1/2 hour, stirring frequently.

title: old fashioned jam cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Thoroughly blend flour mixture into creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in 1 cup jam until blended.

title: whip cream frosting
directions: Boil milk and flour until a heavy paste.
Cool for 10 to 15 minutes.
Beat; then add remaining ingredients.
Beat until creamy.

title: italian sausages
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Add sausage and let brown.
Add tomato paste and water.
If too thick, add more water.
Add spices, using oregano generously.
Let simmer 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine catsup, molasses and mustard together. Stir in bean. Place in 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: oil salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat and stir well.
Chill several hours.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Toss 1 cup of the cheese with kidney beans.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Start layering with taco chips, a layer of cheese-bean mixture, layer of chips and a layer of the meat mixture.
Drizzle the 1/2 cup taco sauce over mixtures.
Top with remaining chips and cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion in hot oil; add beef and seasonings and brown. Add drained beans and soup; pour into greased casserole.
Mash potatoes with milk and egg.
Spoon potato mixture in mounds over meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red wine marinated flank steak
directions: Must be a standing rib, good beef and cannot be frozen before cooking.

title: strawberry fluff dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O
with
cup hot water and 1 cup warm water (not cold).
Mix
in
another bowl, pudding with milk and Cool Whip, then
Jell-O
last.
Refrigerate.
Then top with strawberries. This
can also be make with any flavor of Jell-O and fruit.

title: platte country pie (chocolate chip)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs in a medium bowl.
Add flour, sugar and continue beating for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, butter, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 60 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream or at room temperature.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
In deep mixing bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Continue to beat, slowly adding sugar until stiff meringue forms.
Fold in chocolate pieces.

title: shrimp dip mold
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with blender and set aside.
Heat tomato soup, salt and gelatine until smooth and comes to a boil. Add to cream cheese mixture and mix well.
Put in mold and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours until firm.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: crunchy hot chicken salad
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, broth, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Add chicken, celery, pimento, almonds, water chestnuts, onion, eggs and 1 cup of Ritz cracker crumbs.
Put into casserole dish; top with the remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: french market soup
directions: Wash bean mix; drain.
Add water to cover and salt; soak overnight.
Drain and add 1 1/2 quarts of water, some ham pieces, bay leaf and pinch of thyme.
Simmer 3 hours, covered.
Add tomatoes, onion, clove, garlic, green pepper and salt and pepper to taste.
Also add smoked sausage, cut in thick slices, and several pieces of uncooked chicken.
Simmer until chicken is tender. Remove meat from bone and cut chicken into small pieces, then return to soup.
Ten minutes before serving, add chopped parsley, either fresh or dried.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Put sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed in large microwave-safe mixing bowl.
Bring to boil, then pour over vegetables.
Pack into freezer containers and freeze.
Also good fresh.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup butter Crisco, 1/2 cup sugar and eggs.
Add 2 cups flour, cocoa, salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla, buttermilk and red food coloring.
Mix soda and vinegar and add to above mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat stuffed manicotti
directions: Bring water to a boil; add 1 tablespoon olive oil and pasta. Cook until it is slightly undercooked (pasta will be firm, but not hard).
Drain and rinse in cold water; leave in water.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Let the jello, sugar, hot water and lemon set until mushy. Mix strawberries and whipped topping and fold into jello. Pour over angel food cake bits.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.

title: holiday gelatin salad
directions: Thoroughly dissolve lime gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple with juice to dissolved gelatin.
Allow the mixture to slightly cool.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add yogurt to the mixture and stir in well.
Cool for approximately 15 minutes in refrigerator (or until mixture begins to thicken).
Add sliced cherries and stir well.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over the top of the salad.
Makes 12 servings.
Per serving:
143 calories, 3 grams fat, 0.8 milligrams cholesterol and 70 milligrams sodium.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth; pour into 3 greased cake pans or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: polish apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except: 1 cup flour, 1 stick butter and 1 cup sugar. Spread mixed ingredients onto a greased jelly roll pan. Blend remaining ingredients together to form a crumbly mixture. Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla pudding salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until serving time.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumber and onion.
Cut in thin slices in a salad bowl. Put rest of ingredients in a shaker and shake until well dissolved.
Pour over cucumber and onion.
Mix well.
Serves 6.

title: butter pecan brownies
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 1 egg (beaten) and the melted stick of oleo. Press in 9 x 13 pan. Mix the other stick of oleo, cream cheese, 2 beaten eggs and confectioners sugar. Pour over first layer. Sprinkle chopped pecans over top. Bake at 350° until set.

title: pan de elote(mexican spoon bread)
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add corn, butter, sugar and milk; mix well.
Add Bisquick and mix well, but don't beat to death. Grease rectangular or square baking dish (I use Pam).
Pour half the batter into dish.
Layer to cover with cheese slices.
Next, add the chilies in a loose grid layer.
Cover with another layer of cheese.
Pour remaining batter over, carefully to avoid dislodging the cheese/chilies.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, until top is golden brown.

title: texas goolash
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Boil noodles according to their directions.
Stir chopped onion, Ranch Style Beans, tomato sauce, and water in with meat.
Add noodles and serve.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and chocolate.
Mix until blended.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine braise stew or ham with water and tomatoes.
Let boil slowly for 30 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and cook for 30 minutes more.
Add corn, potatoes and cabbage.
Cook until done. Season to taste with salt, pepper and onion anytime during cooking.
Yields approximately 4 quarts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes on 350°.

title: granny's basic cake batter
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco or butter together.
Add one egg at a time; beat well.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350°.

title: grandma's bread
directions: Mix 3 1/2 cups of flour, the sugar, shortening and yeast in large bowl.
Add warm water and beat together until well mixed. Stir in rest of flour 1 cup at a time until dough is easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Pour out on floured surface and divide in half.
Flatten each half into approximately 18 x 9-inch.
Fold sides crosswise into thirds.
Pinch loaves to seal edge.
Place in 9 x 5 x 3 pan. Brush slightly with melted margarine.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Blend in milk; add eggs, one at a time, alternately with wafers and pecans.
Fold in coconut.
Bake at 250° until toothpick comes out clean.
Bake in greased and floured pan.

title: stromboli
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package directions.
Drain and toss with melted butter or margarine.
Brown ground beef, stirring to crumble; drain.
Stir in cream cheese, chili powder and salt. Simmer 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill shells with beef mixture.
Arrange in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon taco sauce over shells.
Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Uncover; top with cheeses and tortilla chips.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with green onions; garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 main-dish servings.

title: baked peppers and potatoes
directions: Wash peppers and cut into 2-inch pieces.
Wash potatoes and cut into 1-inch slices or chunks.
Do not peel.
Peel onion and cut into chunks.
Put everything in baking dish.
Lightly spray vegetables with olive oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in pan and mix with vegetables.
Boil broth and soup; pour over chicken.
Combine milk, flour and butter; pour over.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Brown 5 to 10 minutes on 450°.

title: fabulous cashew scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, eggs, flour mixture and vanilla; mix well after each addition. Spread batter in prepared pan.
Sprinkle evenly with cashews. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and edges begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool on wire rack before cutting. Cookies freeze well.
Makes 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: leftover roast and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet; add onion and saute over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in canned tomatoes with juice.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat; add cubed, cooked beef or pork.
Simmer covered 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Add parsley if desired.

title: shrimp pasta
directions: In saute pan, melt butter; add garlic.
Add wine and mustard. Add shrimp; cook until they curl.
Remove shrimp to warm plate. Add whipping cream and Cajun seasoning.
To liquid in pan, add cream; reduce by 1/3.
Add Parmesan cheese; stir until melted. Serve over linguine noodles.

title: barbecue sauce for pork or beef
directions: Simmer until all is mixed.
Pour over cooked beef or pork, sliced thin or chunked.
Return to oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender and use immediately.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix all together.
Make small balls (size of a large sour ball).
Press down with tongs of fork.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, but watch!

title: blender hollandaise sauce
directions: Put egg yolks, salt, mustard, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce into blender container.
Cover and process at mix.
Remove blender cap and pour butter in a steady stream until mixture is completely emulsified.
This may be kept warm over hot water in a bowl.
Do not let water boil.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: sourdough biscuits or rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water.
Add buttermilk, oil and sugar.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and flour to make sticky dough.
Place in covered bowl in refrigerator and use as needed. Do not let rise.
Pull off and roll biscuits as needed or put into muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
(Dough will keep in refrigerator 1 week to 10 days.)

title: almond pecan cookies
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add water.
Stir until dough forms ball.
Shape into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.
While warm, roll each in confectioners sugar.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and sugar.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat down to form crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Mix in flour, Krispies and cayenne. Roll into small balls (flatten each with fork).
Cook at 350° until slightly brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Drain, rinse well with cold water and drain again.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all
ingredients except chicken and paprika in a 13 x 9-inch
pan.
Place chicken single layered in pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 25 to 30 minutes. Let stand 3 minutes.

title: hot chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine beans, tomato juice, onion soup and tomatoes and green chilies.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour & sugar. Pour over pineapple which has been put into a greased glass baking dish (small 8x8). Add cheese over top & then sprinkle cracker crumbs on top. Pour melted margarine over all. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: yam-pecan cake with orange frosting
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
In a large mixing bowl, put the cake mix and the chopped pecans.
Mix well.

Add the dissolved gelatin, eggs, oil, mashed yams, grated orange rind and orange juice. Beat according to directions on cake mix package. Pour batter into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Cool cake and top with Orange Frosting.

title: favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg.
Add butter and sugars.
Cream well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet; cookies flatten while baking.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes, or until golden.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: southwestern beef hash
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink.
Pour off drippings. Add mushrooms. Stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Increase heat to medium-high and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in salsa. Continue cooking 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cole slaw mackinac
directions: Trim cabbage; quarter and cut out core.
Shred or finely chop cabbage.
Combine vinegar, lemon juice, chives, parsley, celery seed, sugar, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add cabbage; toss to mix.
Add mayonnaise and toss gently until cabbage is coated. Cover and refrigerate.

title: little pizzas
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Melt cheese into sausage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on bread.
Can freeze on cookie sheet, then bag them.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes until lightly brown on top.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup until it bubbles, add cheese. Mix until smooth. Add gelatin, dissolved in water, onion, pepper and shrimp. Let cool. Add garlic salt and mayonnaise. Chill.

title: marzipan carrot cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a medium bowl; set aside. Combine sugars, buttermilk, vegetable oil, eggs and vanilla extract in large bowl; stir until all ingredients are well blended.
Add flour mixture, carrots, pineapple, walnuts, coconut and raisins, stirring just until well blended.
Grease 3 (8 inch) round cake pans.
Line bottoms with waxed paper.
Grease and flour waxed paper.
Pour batter into cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes; loosen cake layers from edges of pans with sharp knife, and invert onto wire racks.
Peel off waxed paper and cool completely.

title: milanesa de pollo
directions: Beat eggs, salt, pepper and garlic in a shallow bowl.
Pour some of the bread crumbs into a plate.
Slice chicken in half (the long way).
Coat each chicken piece with the egg mixture.
Place coated chicken onto bread crumbs, one at a time.
Turn over, press crumbs firmly into chicken on both sides.
Heat oil to medium heat.
Place chicken in oil and fry until golden on both sides. Remove and place on brown paper to drain.
Serve with fresh lemon.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order as given.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: diane 's strawberry  pie
directions: Wash Strawberries and remove the hull.
Crush 1 cup of small Strawberries and water and cook in saucepan 2 to 3 minutes.
Blend Sugar and Corn Starch into mixture, cook over medium heat until glaze is thick and clear.
Add 3 drops Red Food Coloring to glaze. Place remaining Large Strawberries in baked Pie Shell.
Top with Glaze.
Chill for 4 hours.
Serve with Whip Cream or Cool Whip.

title: baked chicken sandwich
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and spread between the slices of bread.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat eggs; add milk and salt and pour over the sandwiches.
Let stand overnight. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Keep covered the first 35 minutes, then remove cover and sprinkle the almonds on top.
Continue cooking uncovered the rest of the time.

title: sausage bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Put ingredients in middle of dough and spread roll as jelly roll.
Spread egg over roll, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "that cake"
directions: Combine the eggs, oil, water, Dream Whip, pudding, cake mix and vanilla and beat on medium speed with an electric mixer for 7 minutes. Set aside.
Mix together the cinnamon, sugar and walnuts to make the streusel.
In well-greased and floured Bundt pan, pour 1/3 of the cake batter.
Top this with 1/3 of the streusel mixture. Repeat this process 2 more times.
Marbelize and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool 15 minutes and remove from the pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or serve plain.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and cube chicken.
Cook and drain noodles.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in margarine until translucent.
Mix everything together and pour into a 3-quart rectangular casserole.
Top with a little cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 45 minutes at 350°. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: talarena
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper in shortening.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cooked unseasoned corn and rice.
Mix well and pour into buttered 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in jar with tight fitting lid.
Stir rest of ingredients until well mixed.
Pour over cucumbers and cover. Refrigerate 3 days, carefully inverting or stirring each day. Store in refrigerator up to 3 months.

title: scandinavian salmon soup
directions: Combine water, carrots, cauliflower and potato; cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until almost tender.
Drain salmon.
Reserve liquid.
Break into chunks.
Stir flour into salmon liquid and add to soup.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add milk, salmon, peas, dill and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat just until thoroughly heated. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: oatmeal caramel bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat butter on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add about 1 cup of the flour, the brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and the baking soda.
Beat until combined.
Stir in remaining flour then the oats.
Press 2/3 of the dough into an ungreased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces and nuts.
In medium saucepan, combine caramels and milk.
Cook over low heat until melted.
Drizzle over chocolate and nuts.
Drop remaining dough by teaspoons over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is brown.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.
To freeze, wrap in moisture and vaporproof wrap and freeze for up to 6 months.

title: fried peach pies
directions: Remove the peaches from the packages and place them in a medium pan.
Cover with water.
Boil the peaches until soft. Remove from the heat and pour off water.
Put peaches in large bowl.
Mash them with a fork until the texture is very fine.
Add the sugar.
Stir well.
Set aside.

title: sugar biscuits
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/2 or 1/4 to fry until puffed.
Drain.
Put sugar and cinnamon in paper bag and put puffed, fried biscuits in and shake!
You can also use powdered sugar in bag to do the same!

title: deviled eggs with bacon
directions: Cook bacon crisp; crumble and set aside to cool.
Boil eggs well done.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks into mixing bowl and mash with a fork.
Melt butter and let cool.
Add mustard, Miracle Whip, butter, vinegar, salt and pepper; whip with whisk until creamy.
Add bacon bits, then stuff whites.
Chill.
Makes 12 halves.

title: spinach with rice
directions: Wash spinach and drain.
Saute onions in oil until soft.
Add all other ingredients, except rice and cheese.
Cook until spinach is wilted.
Add rice.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender. Remove from heat and add Feta cheese, if desired.
Do not stir. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sedgwick, maine clam chowder
directions: Scrub and steam open raw clams.
Strain and reserve liquid. Coarsely grind or chop clams (or drain minced clams, reserving liquid).
Fry salt pork in large kettle until golden.
Remove pork and reserve; drain off all but 1/4 cup fat.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes.
Add potato, salt, pepper and 4 cups of clam liquid (add water, if necessary).
Simmer until potato is tender.
Add clams, cream, milk and butter.
Heat well.
Add more seasoning, if needed.
Top with pork and paprika.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: sunny green pepper bake
directions: Parboil green peppers for 5 minutes; drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup process cheese.
Combine remaining process cheese, corn and tomato.
Spoon mixture into peppers.
Top with reserved process cheese and crumbs, tossed with butter.
Place peppers in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: excellent pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco,
salt and baking powder.
In a cup, mix egg with vinegar.
Add water to fill cup.
Add to flour mixture.

title: caldo verde
directions: Fry chorizo in a skillet until cooked through.
Drain off excess oil.
Heat chicken broth in a large capacity pot and add cooked chorizo.
Saute onions and garlic in olive oil until translucent, then add chicken broth.
Add potato dices to the soup. Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add greens and simmer 5 minutes more.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: roasted red pepper sauce(for fish)
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise, discard seeds and membranes. Place, skin side up, on foil lined cookie sheet.
Broil 3 inches from heat, 7 to 10 minutes or until skins are blackened.
Place peppers in Ziploc plastic bag for 15 minutes.
Remove from bag, peel off blackened skin.
Combine roasted red peppers, garlic and olive oil in bowl of food processor.
Process until almost smooth. Spoon over grilled fish (or poached).
Keeps 1 week in refrigerator.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Cook until brown.
Mix all remaining ingredients, adding cooled sausage.
Put in greased casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, remove cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Sift sugar, jello and cornstarch in pan.
Add water and cook over medium heat until clear.
Place whole strawberries in pie crust and pour liquid over them.
Chill until firm.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cheese and ham appetizers
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in blender; run until smooth.
Spread mixture 1/8-inch thick on ham slices; roll each slice as for jelly roll.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill an hour or two and slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices on small crackers to serve.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot or roaster.
Cook until meat can be shredded easily with two forks.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into bowl and slice banana into juice. In a large bowl, combine everything, except the walnuts. Refrigerate covered. When ready to serve, mix walnuts in.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening.
Add vanilla and eggs. Add flour, soda and salt into first mixture.
Fold in quick oats and then corn flakes.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown.
Makes a dishpan full.
Good frozen.

title: hobo supper
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Divide ground beef and make 4 patties. Place each patty on a square of foil.
On top of each patty, place onion, carrots and potatoes.
Seal foil around each and place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve in foil; add salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato lasagna
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Cook instant potatoes.
Put sauteed onions with spices, oleo, 2 eggs, 8 ounces Ricotta cheese and potatoes.
Mix 4 ounces Ricotta cheese with grated Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Set aside.
In ungreased pan layer potato mix, noodles, then cheese mix. Alternate, ending with potato mix.
Can add 2 tablespoons milk per layer if you want added moistness.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet. Bake until light golden brown, approximately 7 to 8 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers together and cover with the salt; let stand overnight.
Drain, add the hot peppers, vinegar, spices (tied in cheesecloth bag) and sugar; allow to boil slowly until tender, about 15 minutes.
Add horseradish.
Pack into sterilized Kerr jars to within 1/2-inch of top.
Put on cap, screw band firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes. Yields 6 pints.

title: quiche
directions: Mix eggs and soup in separate bowl; cook meat and drain. Prepare broccoli and strain.
Place 1 cup cheese in each pie shell. Layer 1/2 meat over cheese, then broccoli.
Add 1 can drained mushrooms to each pie.
Pour evenly egg mix over each pie.
Shake lightly to blend.
Bake in 425° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and cook in crock-pot for about 6 hours on low.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter, flour and sugar together until size of peas. Add eggs and beat until fluffy; stir in milk and blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust; sprinkle with nutmeg and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: herbed beer bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cheese and dried herbs. Mix well to combine. Stir in the room temperature beer to produce a stiff batter.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a loaf pan with the shortening and sprinkle bottom and sides with the cornmeal. Turn batter into pan.
Bake at 325° for about 65 minutes. Brush baked loaf with softened butter and sprinkle with additional cornmeal, if desired. Turn out and cool on rack.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Put rice in casserole dish.
Place chicken on rice.
Add soup and water.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Trim off and discard fat from chicken.
In shallow bowl, combine flour, ginger, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken lightly with seasoned flour.
Reserve remaining flour.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, melt 1/2 of margarine.
Add chicken and brown for 5 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken and reserve.
Add remaining margarine, flour and onion to skillet.
Cook, stirring for 3 minutes until onion is softened.
Gradually stir in orange juice.
Add cranberry sauce and honey.
Return chicken to skillet. Cover and simmer on medium heat 20 minutes until cooked through.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water thoroughly.
Boil until mixture will form a firm ball in cool water.
(Use cooking thermometer.) Beat egg white until stiff.
Pour hot syrup slowly over egg white, beating constantly until thick.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Continue beating until stiff enough to drop from teaspoon onto buttered platter.

title: quick minestrone soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in rest of ingredients except pasta and zucchini.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes or until tender.
Stir in pasta and zucchini.
Cook, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheezy broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix 1/2 stick butter.
Melt cheese and mix with broccoli.
Crush crackers.
Melt 1 stick butter and mix with crushed crackers.
Layer broccoli-cheese with crackers.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Mix all other ingredients with pudding and chill.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until it turns clear.
Add jello and food coloring; cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour over fresh peaches in cooked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: *cherry preserves("liko")
directions: Remove pits from cherries and rinse in cold water.

Drain. Place sugar, water and cream of tartar in a large pot and bring to a boil. Boil syrup for 10 minutes and add cherries. Simmer for 40 minutes. Add lemon juice 5 minutes before removing from heat. Cool and pour into clean, dry jars.

title: spoon bread("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Sprinkle corn meal into boiling water gradually, stirring constantly, until smooth and free of lumps.
Add salt, butter and milk and well-beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: king salmon
directions: Drain salmon and reserve liquid.
Flake salmon.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine salmon liquid, catsup and vinegar; heat to boiling.
Add softened gelatin to hot mixture.
Gently blend salmon, celery and onion with hot mixture.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Pour into fish-shaped gelatin mold.
(Crown with a foil crown!)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add to beaten eggs.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Cook in a double boiler until thickened.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff with cream of tartar.
Add sugar.
Put on top of pie.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven until golden brown on top.

title: jim's rabbit
directions: Cut rabbit into serving pieces.
Place in bowl.
Pour Catalina dressing over.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Place rabbit in electric pan.
Pour the dressing over it.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese. Add Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and dash of cayenne pepper. Mix well. Mixture will be very thick. Shape into a round ball and roll around in chopped pecans until well coated. Chill for several hours before serving with crackers or your favorite veggies. Will keep in the refrigerator for 2 weeks if kept wrapped in plastic.

title: salad supreme
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and cool.
Then mix cream cheese, pineapple and mayonnaise; add to cooled Jell-O and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until set.

title: blackberry spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add beaten yolks.
Sift flour, salt and spices together.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Fold in egg whites and add jam, stirring very lightly.
Can be baked in loaf pan or layers.

title: kissie omelette scrambler
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, prepare hash browns according to package directions.
After turning once, sprinkle 2/3 cup of cheese over potatoes.
Transfer to a platter.
In bowl, beat together eggs and milk.
Add ham, chopped pepper, onion and remaining 2/3 cup cheese.
Add egg mixture to skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until eggs are set but still moist.
Spoon egg mixture over center of hash browns.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: fish kabobs
directions: In a shallow pan, arrange the fish cubes in one layer.
Combine the chili sauce, Worcestershire, hot pepper sauce and salt.
Pour over fish and let stand for 1 to 2 hours.
Drain the fish, reserving the marinade.
Cut each piece of bacon into fourths.
On each of 8 skewers, string a fish cube, a piece of bacon, then a square of pepper.
Repeat, ending with a fish cube.
Grill 4 to 5 inches from heat for 10 to 12 minutes, basting a few times with reserved marinade.

title: whiskey sour
directions: Mix well.
Keep in freezer; serve at slush consistency.

title: belgian beef and beer stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in the crock. Cover and cook on low 10 hours or on high 5 hours. Makes about 5 quarts.

title: tuna relish sandwiches
directions: Drain water from the tuna.
Hard boil the eggs and chop into small pieces.
Finely chop the pickles.
Mix all the ingredients together and spread on bread.

title: pull apart bacon cheese wreath
directions: Cut 12-inch square foil and press on bottom and sides of a 9-inch cake pan.
Place inverted custard cup in center of pan. Lightly grease foil and sides of custard cup.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Put 1/2 in a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and put on top of cookies.
Put rest of cookies on top.
Chill overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat butter with soup.
Blend sour cream, onions and cheese into soup, stir until smooth.
Stir in potatoes.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Recipe can be cut in half.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: In a kettle, melt the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well with a large spoon and drop cookie dough by teaspoon
onto waxed paper lined cookie sheets.
Put into refrigerator to cool.
Put into plastic bags or tins to keep.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash, boil and drain.
Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all together.
(It's better to do this and let stand in refrigerator overnight.)
Top with shredded cheese and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; melt in oven.
Pour fruit over butter.
Combine Bisquick, sugar and milk; pour mixture over fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
It is done when the top is slightly browned and firm.

title: apple milkshake(cool and refreshing.  you'll find this recipe requested often.)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover; blend at medium speed for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Makes 3 servings.

title: colonial brown bread
directions: *To substitute for buttermilk, use 1/4 cup vinegar or lemon juice plus milk to make four cups.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; drop on a cookie sheet and bake. Brush with butter and garlic powder.

title: baked ziti
directions: Boil ziti according to the box.
When cooked, drain and put into a 13 x 9-inch roasting pan.
Pour sauce onto ziti and mix. Then, mix the Ricotta cheese into the ziti and sauce mix and over the top, put the Mozzarella cheese (sprinkle) over that.
Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese.
Place in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry pop ice cream
directions: Pour sugar into 6-quart pan.
Add condensed and evaporated milks.
Add strawberry pop, stirring well.
Pour into freezer can. Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk; spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Pour on top cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in greased casserole for 1 hour.
(Very small; I always double recipe.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and apples; set aside.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown pork chops in melted margarine; remove chops.
Cook onion and bell pepper in same skillet.
(I use an old iron skillet).
Add rice, tomatoes and mushrooms and enough water to cook rice.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and cook for 20 to 25 minutes in 325° oven or until rice is done.
Chicken breast can be substituted for pork chops.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Spread potatoes over 1 stick of melted butter or margarine. Mix sour cream, soup and cheese and pour over potatoes.
Melt 1 stick butter or margarine and add corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top. Bake one hour at 350°.

title: cabbage sausage stew
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage until lightly browned. Add potatoes, cabbage and onion. Sprinkle with the oregano, brown sugar, salt (if desired) and pepper. Pour tomatoes over all. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes and cabbage are tender. Serve in bowls. Makes 8 servings.

title: tomato jam
directions: Grind tomatoes.
Add sugar and boil 15 minutes.
Stir often. Add jello, stir and pour into jars.
Cover and freeze.

title: broccoli imperial
directions: Fry bacon crisp; cut up.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons fat. Combine brown sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper; simmer 3 minutes. Pour over bacon, onions and broccoli.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and lemon juice to bananas.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Sift together the dry ingredients. Add with nuts to first mixture, stirring only enough to mix thoroughly.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan (10 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Allow to stand 10 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: asbury vegetable soup
directions: Combine corned beef and vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add frozen vegetables and cook 1/2 hour more.

title: oven baked salmon with dill sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate so that flavors blend.

title: german chocolate delight
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package.
As soon as cake comes out of oven, poke holes in cake with straw.
Immediately pour milk over top.
Cool completely.
When cool, pour ice cream topping over top.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle candy bars on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, mix cabbage and carrots.
In a small bowl, whisk sour cream, vinegar, mayonnaise and milk together.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour over vegetables.
Coat well; refrigerate until serving time.

title: provencale stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off tomatoes; discard.
Carefully scoop pulp into a bowl, leaving shells intact.
Coarsely chop pulp and set aside.

title: lazy day pumpkin loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Yields 2 large and 1 small loaf.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Add mashed potatoes to meat, then add egg, grated onion, catsup, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly; brown in butter, then add 1/2 cup water and steam with top on for 10 minutes.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Crumble 2 pounds cooked hamburger meat in a 3-quart baking dish.
Add the other ingredients, except for the Tater Tots on top.
Cover with foil or lid if you want dry casserole.
Leave uncovered for moister casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters. Sprinkle a little sugar on top before baking.
Bake at 350° 10-12 minutes or until brown.
Don't overbake.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend for 1 minute.

title: lemon delite
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix beef, eggs, onion, oatmeal, catsup and salt.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cut pepper rings and place on top of meat.
Pour one can of mushroom soup over all.
Place frozen Tater Tots on mixture and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: This is a layered salad; do not mix until serving time.
Place prepared spinach in bottom of large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Add prepared bacon.
Do not mix. Add onion and prepared lettuce.
Add the eggs.
Mix mayonnaise and Miracle Whip and pour over eggs.
Cut up the Swiss cheese and place over mayonnaise mixture.
Cover and let the salad set for 24 hours.
Mix and stir just before serving.

title: chilly billy
directions: Brown beef and sausage in heavy pot.
Saute peppers in oil for 5 minutes.
Then add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and parsley.
Stir in chili powder.
Cook 10 minutes and add remaining ingredients EXCEPT beans.
Cook covered.
Simmer 1 hour.
Then add beans.
Let cook on lowest heat for another 1 hour. Stir occasionally.
Keep on lowest heat.

title: quick and easy cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Spread fruit topping over cheesecake.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook meat until tender and add vegetables and onions.
Cook 10 minutes or until done.
Blend cornstarch, ginger, molasses and water.
Add to meat and vegetables and stir until thickened. Serve over cooked rice.

title: mom's homemade peppermint ice cream
directions: Melt the candies in a can of Milnot. Mix with mixer all ingredients, including the melted candies.

title: radiatore chicken soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients except Radiatore.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until chicken is no longer pink and carrots are tender.
Meanwhile, cook Radiatore according to package instructions, approximately 10 to 12 minutes. Take care not to overcook.
Drain pasta; add to soup and serve immediately.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients until the consistency of dressing.
Put in buttered casserole dish and cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Cut orange into 8 wedges.
Insert 3 cloves into rind of each wedge.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in 3-quart saucepan.
Stir until sugar is dissolves.
Add orange wedges. Bring mixture to simmer over medium heat, stirring occasionally. (Do not boil.)
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Simmer wassail for 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Coat baking pan with canola oil.
Set aside.
Thaw fish if frozen.
Rinse and dry with paper towels.
Cut into 4-inch pieces.

title: seasoned salt blend 2(salt free)
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.

title: german potato cheese soup
directions: Cook until tender the potatoes, onion, pepper, carrots, 5 cups water and chicken bouillon cubes.
Add cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
(You can use 1 cup chopped celery instead of 1 can cream of celery soup.)

title: carrot cake
directions: In a separate bowl, mix flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda. In a bowl, beat together sugar, eggs and oil until well blended. Add grated carrots and pineapple.
Add flour mix and vanilla; mix. Bake at 350° in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan 45 minutes. Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: funny cake pie
directions: Blend together the sugar and butter.
Stir in egg yolks, milk, flour and lemon juice.
Beat 2 egg whites and then add to the above mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in oven at 325 for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Top will be like sponge cake, bottom like custard.

title: upside-down cake(diabetic)
directions: Drain cherries (or fruit) and save juice for Cherry Sauce. Spread cherries over bottom of greased shallow loaf pan.
Cream margarine with sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt; add alternately with milk to first mixture. Add flavoring and Sucaryl solution.
Pour over cherries and bake. Serve warm with Cherry Sauce.

title: harold's biscuits
directions: Mix dough ingredients together and add enough milk to make a light puffy dough.
Roll dough in flour.
Flour hands and pastry board.
Roll dough, using a biscuit cutter or glass to cut out biscuits.
Toss hand to hand; shake off excess flour.
Grease top. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: biscuits for shortcake
directions: Mix as for pie crust.
Place on floured board and roll for about 8 biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9-inch pie pan.

title: old-fashioned sour cream cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture alternately with sour cream. Divide dough; roll out 1/4 inch thick on well floured pastry cloth.
Cut with a 2-inch cutter; place on a greased baking sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: white christmas fruitcake
directions: Toss together raisins, peels, candied fruits and nuts with 1/2 of the flour.
Beat shortening and butter together.
Add sugar gradually.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Resift remaining 4 cups flour with baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with pineapple juice, beating well after each addition.
Stir in fruit mixture.
Sprinkle cream of tartar over egg whites.
Beat until stiff enough to hold peaks but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Spoon batter into 10-inch tube pan lined with well-greased and floured brown paper.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 3 hours.
Place shallow pan of water on bottom of oven during baking.
When done, remove and cool on rack, pulling paper down from sides but leave attached.
When cooled, pull up paper around sides.
Overwrap in foil and store in cool place.
Makes a 5 pound cake.

title: onion bread
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion to butter and cook in microwave until tender, 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon on French bread between slices. Wrap in foil.
Warm in oven 10 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel candy
directions: Cook sugar, buttermilk and soda in a large pan until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Then add margarine, vanilla and pecans.
Stir until thick and pour into a buttered dish.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate meat for several hours, mixing occasionally.
Broil or bake the usual time, basting before turning and as needed to coat meat evenly.

title: ribs 'n' kraut
directions: Cut ribs into serving size pieces. Brown on both sides in frypan.
Season with salt and pepper. Place sauerkraut into large casserole. Add onion slices and ribs.
Pour water in frypan.
Stir to loosen drippings. Pour over ribs.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch or 3 (8-inch) layer pans or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers, 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Mix egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cookies should be soft in center when removed from oven.
Bake in an 8-inch square pan.

title: frozen crab salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with mayonnaise, Tabasco and salt. Fold in whipped cream.
Blend in crab, celery, green pepper, carrot and onion.
Pour into freezer tray.
Freeze until solid, about 6 to 8 hours.
Remove from freezer and allow to stand at room temperature for about 15 minutes before slicing.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 8.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Using solid shortening, grease and flour bottom only of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In large bowl, blend all ingredients until blended. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes. Remove from pan.
Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: "stretcher" oyster stew
directions: Perfect to fix when oyster supply is scarce--potatoes are the "stretchers."

title: janne's chicken delight
directions: Mix all soups and rice together in a large shallow baking pan lined with foil.
Spray foil with vegetable spray.
Lay 6 chicken breasts on top of sauce.
Melt 1 stick of real butter.
Pour over top of breasts.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Chill until jello thickens but is not set.
Chop cranberries (washed and drained), celery, oranges and apples very finely.
Add these, pineapple and nuts to jello mixture.
Stir well.
Can be put in fancy mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: barley peasant soup
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown meat in oil.
Add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook until beef is no longer pink.
Add water and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots and barley.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 to 60 minutes or until barley is tender.
Add beans, zucchini, tomatoes, cabbage, parsley and seasonings.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Top individual bowls with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic.
Drain.
Pour tomato sauce over meat.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, paste, salt, sugar and pepper. Simmer for about 2 hours.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit, pecans and 3/4 cup flour.
Mix butter and sugar until smooth.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and add to butter and sugar.
Add the cup of flour, baking powder, salt and flavoring.
Mix well, adding to fruit and pecan mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 250° to 275° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into cake.

title: wonderful fruit dip
directions: Make pudding using milk.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Add Amaretto. Serve with fruit cut into bite-sized pieces.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve 1 package yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix in bowl butter, sugar and salt.
Pour scalded milk over and add flour and egg and mix with mixer.
Add yeast when batter is warm.
Add flour. Turn on floured board (rest 10 minutes).
Place in well greased crock, raise 2 hours and punch down.
Shape in rolls and raise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; cube cooked chicken.
(Don't use the skin.) Add rest of ingredients to chicken; mix well.
Put in flat pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into 4-inch squares.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine filling ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Sprinkle with Crunchy Topping.

title: crispy baked barbecued chicken
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Combine bread crumbs, brown sugar, chili powder, garlic powder, dry mustard, celery seed and cayenne. Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brush each chicken piece with melted butter.
Roll in crumb mixture to coat.

title: ice box cookies
directions: Mix ingredients as you would any cookies. Place firm dough in a lined (use foil or wax paper) pan and cover well.
Place dough in refrigerator over night. Next day, uncover dough & slice cookies into squares. Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Brown the meat slightly and drain.
To the meat, add the rice, 1 egg, 1/2 cup chopped onion, 1 tablespoon parsley and 1/4 teaspoon each of garlic powder, paprika, pepper and salt.
Mix well.

title: texas trash(from the files of diana miller crutchfield)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Melt 1 pound oleo plus 1/2 cup bacon drippings and add the spices, Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke.
Pour liquid over cereals, etc. and stir well.
Bake slowly at about 200°, stirring frequently for 1 1/2 hours or until mixture feels dry.
When completely cool, store in containers and it will keep indefinitely.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer ingredients in baking dish starting with crushed Doritos and ending with as much cheese as desired.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: baked beans and hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger and mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° covered for 30 minutes.
Uncover, and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: cereal cookies (chewy)(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Cream together sugars and Crisco. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add this to creamed mixture; mix well. Stir in cereal. Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: beef casserole
directions: Place beef in casserole; cover with undiluted soup.
Cover and bake for 3 hours in 300° oven. Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: stuffed pork tenderloin
directions: Flatten tenderloins between pieces of plastic wrap until they are about 1/4-inch thick.
Be careful not to tear them.
Mix mushrooms, cheese, salt and pepper and lay on the top of the largest tenderloin.
Top with second tenderloin and sew the two together.
Dredge in flour, then in eggs and then in bread crumbs. Refrigerate for at least an hour.
In a large ovenproof skillet with a lid, brown the meat on both sides, turning carefully with 2 spatulas.
Do not use high heat.
When brown, remove from heat and add the wine; cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove to serving platter; remove string and pour juices over before carving.

title: cranberry and nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
In another bowl, add beaten egg, liquid shortening, juice and water.
Add to the dry ingredients and mix until just moist.
Add chopped nuts and the cranberries, which have been cut in halves.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 325° oven in a greased loaf pan.
Cool.
Place in plastic bag or foil to freeze.
This is better after it sets a day.

title: baked fish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make paste with crackers and butter.
Pat fish dry.
Add salt and pepper; sprinkle with lime juice.
Roll in cracker and butter paste until covered.
Place in 8 x 10-inch Pyrex dish.
Crumble remaining cracker paste on top.
Place in a brown paper bag; seal tight.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and put in medium size pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: best ever pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Stir in pumpkin, eggs, oil and nuts. Mix until combined.
Spoon into greased muffin tins or use paper liners.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Peel squash, diced and cooked until slightly tender.
Set aside.
Melt 1 stick butter and add 1 package of Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Stir and mix well.

On the bottom of the baking dish put in 1/3 of the stuffing mixture and put in the combined onion, soup, carrot and sour cream added to the cooked squash. Then top with the remaining stuffing mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered with foil.
Remove foil and cook for another 15 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Pour over the other ingredients and mix well.
Let set overnight in the fridge.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; spoon into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with sliced green onions and tomato.
Serve with tortilla chips, crackers or bread.

title: italian gnocchis
directions: Make potatoes according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Knead until blended and smooth.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 1-inch strips.
Then cut each strip into 1/2-inch or so inch pieces.
Press into each piece with tins of a fork or with index finger or second finger pressed into each.
Roll off gently to make a round barrel with a hollow center.

title: punch
directions: Add water to make 2 gallons.

title: chicken-style rice(non-dairy)
directions: Saute onion, pepper, mushrooms, celery and soymeat in margarine.
Mix pimentos, olives and peas together.
Combine all ingredients.
Good to refrigerate awhile before serving if serving cold.
Can be served warm, too.

title: peachy cream cheese
directions: Shape cream cheese into a 4 1/2-inch circle on a serving dish. Chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and cut squash in 2-inch pieces.
Dice onions.
Put both in large pan with water to cover the vegetables; salt and pepper. Boil until soft.
Drain water and mash squash and onions; let cool. Add egg, mayonnaise, sugar, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish and cover with shredded cheese and Ritz crackers.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: karen's great white cake
directions: Make the white cake according to directions on package.
Cool 10 minutes.
Poke holes with a fork.
Pour 1 can of cream of coconut over cake.
Cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: red beans and rice with sausage
directions: Melt butter and saute vegetables until soft.
Stir in beans, broth, water and seasoning.
Bring to boil and stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers and combine with butter and sugar. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream large package of cream cheese.
Add 2 eggs, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat well and spread over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool and then pour over top the pie filling.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream.
Serves 12.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add flavorings.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add alternately the measured flour and milk.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° in round pound cake pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine the margarine, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat the eggs.
In another bowl, combine the flours, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add this to the wet ingredients, blending well.
Stir in the chocolate chips and the nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto Teflon or ungreased baking sheets.
Bake until golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies, 2-inches in diameter.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown chuck & onion together.
Drain & pour into casserole dish, add salt, pepper, garlic powder & worcestershire sauce. Arrange cheese slices over top of meat.
Mix gravy mix with one cup water, pour over cheese.
Arrange tater tots to cover completely.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: canja(chicken soup)
directions: Put all ingredients except rice in a large kettle.
Cook over low heat, cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove chicken pieces and set aside.
Add rice and continue cooking until tender.
Remove bay leaf, chop chicken pieces and return to broth.
Skim off excess fat with spoon before serving.
Reduce the heat to low, cover tightly and simmer for 30 minutes or until the meat is tender and shows no resistance when pierced with the point of a small, sharp knife.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Crust: Mix the first 4 ingredients; spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Cut angel food cake into 1-inch cubes.
Make instant pudding as directed with skim milk.
Layer half of the cake in punch bowl. Spread half the pudding over the cake.
Follow with half of the pineapple and then one can of pie filling, followed by half of the Cool Whip.
Repeat second layer of ingredients, topping with Cool Whip.
Decorate with maraschino cherries.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine first five ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 8-inch square pan/dish. Separate biscuits and arrange over mixture. Bake 20 minutes or until golden and bubbly, covering loosely with foil after 12 minutes. Serve with salad.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel and core about 10 good baking apples.
Place the halves in a baking dish with the open centers up.
Crumble together brown sugar and flour.
Sprinkle this mixture over the apples, then sprinkle well with cinnamon.
Dot each apple center with a piece of butter.
Add enough boiling water so that it comes about halfway up on the apples.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: excellent blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
In separate small bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture with milk alternately.
Stir until moist.
Fold in blueberries and walnuts. Fill greased or papered muffin tins about 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: berry fritters
directions: Wash and clean 2 pints of berries. Sprinkle with sugar and flour. Divide into six portions. Set aside.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Mix together; put in a baking dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Let jello cool and add pineapple.
Whip cream cheese in mixer and add cream gradually.
Mix together and chill.

title: joe's chuck roast
directions: Flour both sides of chuck; brown well in small amount of oil. Add water, onions, garlic, vinegar, coffee, allspice, salt and pepper.
Bring to simmer and cook 4 hours or until very tender. Add brown gravy mix (mixed with 1/2 cup cold water).
Simmer for 10 minutes more.
Add mushrooms; simmer 10 minutes until cooked through.
Great with
steamed green beans and mashed potatoes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and chopped onion in small amount of oil in a heavy skillet.
Cook slowly until meat has turned white; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with a tossed salad and garlic bread.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake	in
a
10 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix the oatmeal with the hot water and let stand 10 minutes. Beat together the sugars and margarine.
Add the eggs and beat. Add the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add the oatmeal and blend.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is baking, make the topping.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Stir lemon juice into milk.
Set in refrigerator while whipping cream.
Fold cream into milk mixture.
Add extracts. Pour into crust and chill 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon pie filling on top and chill.
Makes 9-inch pie.

title: quick chocolate pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars and mix into Cool Whip.
Spread into prebaked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: taco salad dressing
directions: Shake or mix well.
Add to the salad.

title: olive cheese puffs
directions: Mix olives, onion, cheese, mayonnaise and curry powder together.
Split muffins in half and spread the mixture evenly over the 12 halves.
Lay plastic wrap over them and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Cut each muffin half into 6 wedges.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, blend margarine, sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: oatmeal hamburgers
directions: Beat eggs and combine all other ingredients with them.
Drop from spoon to form small patties.
Brown on both sides in hot shortening.
Cover with water in which a rounded teaspoon of Vegex was dissolved.
Simmer 45 minutes on top of stove or in oven.
The liquid will boil away, leaving delicious patties.

title: impossible calico corn and bacon pie
directions: Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Reserve two tablespoons of the bacon.
Mix remaining bacon, the onion, green pepper, corn and pimentos in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients, except sour cream, until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake in 400° oven uncovered until knife inserted comes out
clean, about 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes. Garnish with sour cream and reserved bacon.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add flour and cinnamon. Mix together.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chips pecan cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla until creamy. Add rest of ingredients.
Drop rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: chewy bread pretzels
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and salt. Blend in flour, one cup at a time, to form a soft dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down and divide into 15 equal portions.
Roll each portion into a 14-inch rope.
Shape into traditional pretzel shape and place on a greased baking sheet.
Brush pretzels with egg and sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 15 pretzels.

title: pasta with seafood marinara sauce
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients over medium heat for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Add raw shrimp, continuing to simmer over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Shrimp should turn very pink.
Serve sauce over hot angel hair pasta (cappelini) or vermicelli and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6. This recipe won 3rd place in the Greenville Down East Cookoff in 1992.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar in saucepan. Stir in the milk and bring to a boil.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool 10 minutes. To make creamy frosting, cool Caramel Icing 10 minutes, then blend in 1 cup sifted confectioners sugar.

title: dad's favorite fudge
directions: Grease 8 x 8 pan.
Combine all ingredients except butter and vanilla.
Stir to blend.
Set over low heat, stirring slowly; bring to a boil.
Cover pot and let boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Uncover and brush sides of pot with pastry brush dipped in cold water. Continue to boil slowly without stirring until syrup reaches soft-ball stage (235°).

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute green peppers and onion in butter.
Add all the other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients; dip into bread crumbs.
Form into cakes and dip in bread crumbs again.
Fry or broil until brown on both sides.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Coat balls with coconut or finely chopped pecans.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat broth to boiling point.
Slightly beat the egg; add the flour and salt to egg and beat until smooth.
Pour egg batter in a fine stream into boiling broth, stirring while pouring.
Sprinkle parsley flakes.
Serve immediately.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar gradually.
Add one egg at a time.
Beat well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and milk. Add flavoring.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: **red christmas punch
directions: Boil sugar with 1/2 gallon water just so sugar is dissolved; then cool.
Add other ingredients.
Serve with crushed ice. (Serves 30 people.)

title: orange fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except greens; toss lightly with Citrus Dressing.
Chill.
Pour into a bowl lined with salad greens.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses; add other ingredients, except nuts, and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli for 4 minutes and drain.
Whisk together mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, grated onion, eggs and pepper.
Mix with broccoli.
Melt 1 cup butter.
Mix with diced bread until butter is absorbed.
Add broccoli mixture to 9 x 11-inch casserole.
Cover with diced bread.
Bake for 45 minutes uncovered at 350°.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Boil sugar, water, fruit, shortening, salt and spices together in a saucepan about 3 minutes.
Cool and add flour and baking powder which have been sifted together.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan in a moderate oven about 45 minutes.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water; set aside.
In bowl, mix meat, 1/4 cup onion, crumbs, egg and 1/4 cup bouillon liquid; shape into 16 meatballs.
In large skillet brown meatballs in oil; remove from pan.
Add remaining onion; cook until tender.
Stir in flour then remaining bouillon liquid, Worcestershire sauce and meatballs until smooth.
Cover, simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: corn pudding
directions: Polk salad is a plant that grows wild.
Pick and wash polk salad.
Place in a pot and boil for about 1/2 hour.
Pour off water and boil a second time for about 1/2 hour and drain.
Place oil in a skillet.
Add onions; simmer.
Add polk salad.
Cook at low temperature.
Add eggs, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until eggs are well done.

title: date nut salad
directions: Blend together cream cheese and crushed pineapple.
Add dates and nuts.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in a long dish and put in the freezer until frozen.
Cut into squares and place on lettuce leaf. Serves 10.

title: rye rounds
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage, then add Velveeta.
Spread on rye bread.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight or at least a few hours.
Will keep for several days.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Measure warm water into a large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast and stir until it dissolves.
Add salt, sugar and flour.
Mix and knead dough. Get a small ball of dough and roll and twist into shapes. Grease cookie sheet, lay pretzel on cookie sheet.
Brush pretzels with beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seeds.

title: lasagne(low calorie)
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic in saucepan until redness disappears.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles.
In a casserole dish, spread 1/3 meat, then 1/2 noodles, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese.
Repeat once and lastly top off with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or cover with waxed paper for 20 minutes, rotating every 8 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: meat timbles
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Line ungreased muffin pans with meat mixture to a thickness of 1/4-inch.
Fill with mashed potatoes.
Bake in moderate oven, 350° for 30 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle cheese 10 minutes before they are done.

title: molasses spice cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and beat well.
Add molasses. Sift flour with baking soda and spices.
Beat well.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Then drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Dip a fork into sugar and flatten cookie in a crosshatch design.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.

title: garden salsa
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 12 ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with chips. Yields 5 cups.

title: panzarella
directions: Combine all ingredients and allow to sit at room temperature for 30 or more minutes.
Serve on leafy lettuce with crusty bread.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and biscuits into large bowl.
Tear loaf bread into pieces and add to cornbread.
Tear chicken into pieces. Add sage, eggs, salt, onions and pepper.
Pour chicken broth in until mixture is completely saturated.
Melt butter.
Pour 1/2 into baking pan.
Pour dressing mixture into pan.
Top with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Let dissolve.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.

title: pecan jam
directions: Put in a pan large enough to hold all and allow stirring.
Heat in open pan until all ingredients blend and are rich in golden color.
Can be canned in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, bread cubes, milk and cheese together until bread cubes are saturated.
Add browned sausage.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Allow mixture to set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dad's favorite cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla together until fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Beat into mixture.
Stir in rolled oats.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until brown.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Boil rice until fluffy. Saute onion and bell pepper in butter. Add soup, lemon juice, pepper and garlic salt. Stir and add to rice. Add shrimp and parsley. Mix and place in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese on top. Dot the top with butter. May decorate with parboiled bell pepper rings if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Make stuffing according to package directions (reserve some for topping).
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken on top.
Mix sour cream and soup together; spread over chicken. Sprinkle reserved stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: grandmother's ginger cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oleo.
Add molasses, coffee with soda dissolved in it and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased tray.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat with onions, salt, and pepper.
Cook until done and drain.
Add tomatoes and let cook about 15 minutes. Shred both cheeses.

title: eggs imperial
directions: Mix soup and sherry.

Saute butter and mushrooms until brown. In large casserole dish, layer 3/4 of cream sauce, 1/2 of the cheese, add mushrooms and eggs, remaining sauce and then top with remaining cheese. Place under broiler until golden brown and bubbly.
If made ahead of time, refrigerate.
Then bake in preheated oven (350°) about 30 to 40 minutes.
