Great for a brunch.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Put about a teaspoon of dough on a waffle iron.
Place on medium heat, one in each section, and bake for 1 minute.
Frost, if desired.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400°
for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease an 8-inch pan.

Combine butter and cocoa in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth. Remove from heat; stir in sugar, egg, flour, buttermilk and vanilla. Mix until smooth. Spread evenly in pan. Bake 25 minutes. Do not overbake. Remove from oven. Sprinkle marshmallows, walnuts and chocolate chips over the top. Bake for 3 to 5 minutes or until topping is melted.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients and bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy chip or vegie dip
directions: Spoon sour cream into medium size bowl. Stir in one of the soup mixes. Excellent with your favorite chips or vegies.

title: granola bars (balls)
directions: For bars, butter a 9-inch pan or for balls, have waxed paper on table.
In a 3-quart saucepan, boil corn syrup for 1 minute only, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Stir in granola. Work fast as it hardens quickly. Spread or pat in pan or let kids make into balls.
(Best to grease hands to make balls.)

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Poke holes in cake and pour 1/4 cup Kahlua over holes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut cake into squares.
Layer bottom of dish with cake, then mousse, then Cool Whip.
Repeat layering.
Sprinkle top of dessert with crushed Skor bars.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cube 2 slices of bread in baking dish.
Combine chicken and chopped vegetables, salt and mayonnaise.
Spread over bread. Crumble rest of bread on top of mixture.
Combine milk and eggs. Pour mixture over; cover and chill 1 hour or overnight.

title: maryland crab imperial
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Instead of layering as in a restaurant, we used ice cream scoop to shape in rows in a baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika over each scoop for a nice presentation. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's chicken
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken and brown well. Season with salt, pepper and paprika; cook for 10 minutes.
Cut potatoes in 1-inch cubes.
Cut bacon in 1-inch pieces and cook for 5 minutes.
Add onions and beef bouillon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 5 minutes to brown the chicken.
Arrange on platter and garnish with parsley.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, almost tender (6 to 7 minutes).
Drain.
Combine all remaining ingredients except cherries and cinnamon-sugar.
Blend well.
Stir into hot noodles. Pour half the noodle mixture into large 4-quart baking or roasting pan.
Spread cherries over surface.
Add remaining noodle mixture. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with sour cream if desired. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, then sour cream, mixing well after each addition.
Add soda, flour and vanilla. Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Fold into lightly greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Recipe dates back to 1932.
Flour (just enough to knead until dough will not stick to hands), will take approximately 4 to 5 pounds flour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Reserving
2 egg whites for meringue, combine remaining ingredients and
pour
into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: krab salad
directions: Mix and pour a little milk in to thin mixture.	Great!

title: danish puff
directions: Mix butter and water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flavoring.
Stir in flour immediately to prevent lumping. When smooth and thick, add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Divide in half and spread evenly over each piece of pastry.
Bake about 50 to 60 minutes, until topping is crisp and brown, at 350°.
Frost when cool.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, granulated and powdered sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat eggs.
Add salt and add to creamed mixture.
Add oil and vinegar.
Blend well.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to mixture.
Take pieces of dough, about the size of a walnut.
Roll into a ball and place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on each ball.
Use a glass tumbler with fancy design on bottom.
Dip into sugar and press dough flat. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add to hot broth and mayonnaise.
Mix in mustard and horseradish.
Add chicken, eggs, peas, celery, olives, pimento and almonds.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Chill at least 8 hours.

title: mexican dip
directions: Use a pie dish.
Spread the bean dip on the bottom.
Beat the cream cheese and then spread onto bean dip.
Spread chopped chili peppers over cream cheese.
Dice the onion and pepper on top according to your taste.
Shred cheese and distribute evenly. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: 89'er biscuits
directions: Mix biscuit mix with honey and pecans.
Add water to form soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Cut with floured cutter.
Place, lightly touching, on greased cookie sheet.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Top with glaze.

title: apple bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until fine.
Add eggs and blend well.
Mix together grated apple, orange rind and milk.
Add to mixture and stir to blend just until smooth.
Turn into well-greased pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Slices best 1 day old.

title: toast - buttered
directions: Take bread.
Take butter.
Put the butter on the bread and cook.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Mix the ingredients and bake at 375° for about 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry nut salad(make day or evening before)
directions: Use 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix together and congeal.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt to taste.

title: kuglei
directions: Cook bacon; chop fine.
Reserve grease.
Combine all ingredients, including bacon grease.
Place in 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: philly 3-step cheesecake bars
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix until blended. Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into 8-inch square baking pan, that has been lined with foil.
Pour batter over crust. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool; refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Cut into bars. Yield:
16 servings.

title: chinese wrap-ups
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter.
Add water chestnuts, shrimp and soy sauce.
Flatten biscuits.
Put 1 teaspoon of filling into each biscuit and pinch together to close. Put on greased baking pan and bake for 10 minutes at 475°.
Serve hot.

title: french cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in 1 cup coffee or water.
Combine with all other ingredients except powdered sugar and the water or milk used for it.
Bake in 2 (9 x 12 x 3-inch) pans.
While warm, frost with powdered sugar icing made by combining sugar with a little water or milk until creamy.
Cut into squares.
This was my mother's recipe.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil until creamy.
Combine egg yolks and hot water.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add carrots and mix.
Combine all dry ingredients and sift together.
Add flour and nuts to creamed mixture.
Then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased angel food pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blue cheese tenderloin steaks
directions: Combine cream cheese, Blue cheese, yogurt, onion and pepper; reserve.
Rub each side of beef steaks with garlic.
Place steaks on rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 2 to 3 inches from heat.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes.
Season with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Turn and broil 3 to 4 minutes.
Season with remaining salt.
Top each steak with an equal amount of reserved cheese mixture.
Broil an additional 1 to 2 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into a large thick meat loaf or put in a loaf pan.
Bake one hour in 350° oven or until brown.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish and line with graham crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare hamburger, onion and taco seasoning mix according to directions on package.
Tear lettuce in a large bowl.
Add tomatoes and cheese.
Crumble Doritos in the bag.
Mix everything together and enjoy.
Really good with Ranch dressing.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: In medium bowl, beat together eggs, onion soup & salt. Add broccoli & cheese. Pour into greased 9 inch pie plate or quiche dish. Bake in preheated 375 degree oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes. To serve, cut in wedges.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in large bowl.
Add brown sugar, salt and Karo. Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 2 more minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir.
Microwave 1 minute.
Pour over popped corn in large brown paper bag.
Stir and shake well.
Close and turn bag upside down.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake well.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake well.
Stir.
Microwave 45 seconds.
Shake well.
Stir.
Microwave 30 seconds.
Shake well. Stir.
Cool on cookie sheet or foil.

title: stromboli
directions: Mix together the eggs, oregano and salt and pepper.
Unthaw bread dough 3 hours.
Grease an 18 x 12-inch pan.
Spread dough to fit sheet.
Brush with 1/2 egg mixture.
Layer meat and cheese. Roll like a jelly roll.
Pinch all ends shut.
Brush top with egg mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown, 35 minutes.
Serve hot.
Cut in slices.
Top with spaghetti sauce.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Boil 2 bags of rice as instructed on box.
While rice is cooking, lightly brown sesame seeds in peanut oil, then set aside. Chop green onions and grate carrots.
When rice is cooked, remove bags from water and drain.
Break chicken into small pieces and add to sesame seeds in oil.
Add rice, chopped green onions, bean sprouts, mushrooms and grated carrots.
More oil can be added.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Use 1 bag of rice for 2-3 servings.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and make balls.
Mix next 4 ingredients, pour over balls.
Bake, covered with foil, 1 hour at 350° then, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Brown ribs on all sides.
Melt margarine in pan.
Add onion and brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until flavors are blended, about 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over browned ribs.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.
Serves 6 normal people.

title: mom's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.

title: hungry man's casserole
directions: Saute onions.
Add remaining ingredients, except for biscuits. Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place biscuits on top of beans and meat mixture.

title: apple muffins
directions: Beat together the egg, juice or milk, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, sugars, baking powder, salt and apple.
Mix all ingredients.
Fill muffin cups.
Sprinkle tops of muffins with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: richard's favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir in by hand.
Fold in pecans, corn flakes and oatmeal.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: cashew beef bake
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain well.
Saute beef, onions and celery in butter over medium heat.
Put meat mixture and noodles in two layers in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper and pour over beef and noodles.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Sprinkle with cashews and cook for 10 minutes more.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat oil (2 inches deep).
After you mix batter, pour it into the hot oil, moving it in a circular motion then in a crisscross pattern until you have made a cake about the size of a small doughnut.
When lightly browned, remove from oil and drain on paper towel.
While hot dredge them in powdered sugar.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine and chill until firm, then put on a topping of:

title: poor man's meal
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix beans and barbecue sauce into the browned mixture.
Put into deep dish (baking dish).
Cut biscuits in half and place around the side of dish on top of the mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 325° until done.

title: easy oven baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes and onions into 1/4-inch slices.
Alternate slices, slightly overlapping, in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine margarine, garlic, salt, pepper and celery seed; drizzle over potatoes and onions.
Cover and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with the paprika and bake uncovered for 20 additional minutes.

title: deer steak
directions: Mix flour, onions and seasoning.
Put butter in pan or foil. Sprinkle flour mixture on both sides of meat.
Use plenty of butter.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 4 hours at 350°.
Turn every 20 minutes or so.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Makes 1 quart dry mix. Put desired amount of mix into cup; add boiling water and stir.

title: chicken salad
directions: Drain marinated chicken and mix well with other ingredients. (Rice is optional and may be used to stretch recipe.)
Serve with hot rolls and a dessert for a luncheon.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix melted butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mash bananas.
Add baking soda to mashed bananas and mix.
Add banana mixture to butter mixture.
Mix in flour.
Beat 350 strokes.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies in a blender or food processor. Divide cookies into 3 equal portions.
Using a mixer, cream together the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Mix the milk and pudding.
Add whipped cream.
Combine the two mixtures.
Layer 1/3 of the cookies, half of the mixture, 1/3 of the cookies and the other half of the mixture. Sprinkle the rest of the cookies on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add well beaten eggs. Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture. Add milk and vanilla. Roll tissue thin on floured board.
Cut cookies.
Bake in a 350° oven about 10 minutes.

title: pat's truffles
directions: Place chocolate chips in large, grease-free bowl, preferably stainless steel.
Heat whipping cream in small saucepan over low heat until bubbles start to form on top.
Do not boil!
Add to chocolate chips and beat until melted.
Beat for about 5 minutes after they have melted until starting to thicken.
Refrigerate until very cold.
Using a melon baller or teaspoon, scoop out 1 teaspoon at a time.
Roll in palms until ball forms.
They will be uneven.
Don't worry, that is how good truffles look.
After rolling into balls, dip in cocoa until thoroughly covered.
Put in waxed paper lined boxes and keep refrigerated.
May be frozen, but they become soggy if frozen longer than a week.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
(Dice and peel potatoes before boiling.)
Cook until potatoes are soft.
Drain.
Add chopped onion, relish, mayonnaise, mustard (to taste), paprika and eggs. Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with paprika on top.
Serve warm or refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: tiny open-faced sandwiches
directions: Mix together and spread on tiny slices of party rye bread. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: recipe for a good cook
directions: Blend all ingredients and allow to rise until doubled.
Mold into your lifestyle.
Bake with kindness.
Serve everyday. Guaranteed to bring a smile to the face, a light to the eyes and a compliment to the cook.

title: company chicken
directions: Place spinach on bottom of baking dish. Wrap chicken breast around a piece of cream cheese. Place seam side down on spinach. Mix soup, sour cream and wine together. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Beat together ingredients, except pecans.
Mix in pecans. Pour in pie shell.
Bake until set and pie shell is browned at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: quick veg soup
directions: Brown beef in small amount oil.
Add water, tomatoes and beef and vegetable bouillons.
Simmer 1 hour, more if needed.
Add vegetables and seasoning.
Simmer 1 hour or until vegetables and meat are done.
Great for unexpected company and nourishing too.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs
well,
but
do
not overbeat.
Add sugar and Karo. Melt
margarine
and
add
to egg mixture with salt and vanilla. Mix
well
and add pecans.	Put in unbaked crust and bake at 400° for
15 minutes;
then at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Stir in milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add all other ingredients over low heat.
Transfer to hollowed out dark bread and serve dip with bread pieces.
Serve warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese. Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Add garlic to taste.
Refrigerate to harden.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nut pieces.
Wrap and chill in refrigerator.
Much better flavor if made a day or two before serving.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine and chips.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and pecans.
Press 1/2 of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, milk, vanilla, and egg.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken mein and vegetables in creamy szechuan dressing
directions: Skin, bone and halve chicken breasts (or use boneless).
Poach and cool.
Cut into bite size pieces and reserve.
Cook noodles in 4 quarts boiling water until very al dente.
Drain and toss in large bowl with 1/2 cup soy sauce, then peanut oil.
Cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally, to coat thoroughly.

title: hummus tahini
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Let stand several hours for flavors to permeate.
Serve with pita bread.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine bananas, lemonade and orange juice in blender and blend until smooth.
Combine other ingredients except lemon-lime soda. Mix well and freeze.
Thaw until mushy, add soda and serve.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: tuna patties
directions: Drain tuna.
Whirl oatmeal in blender to a fine grain.
Chop onion in blender.
Mix with tuna and egg.
Shape into 4 patties and deep fry to golden brown.

title: apple crisp cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix good and put in Pyrex long dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until lightly golden brown.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, but the buttered bread crumbs.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Add the buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: curried apple salad
directions: Core and cube apples.
In a large bowl, combine apples, celery, nuts and raisins.
In a small bowl, blend together remaining ingredients.
Pour over apple mixture; toss lightly with fork until apple pieces are well coated.
Serve on crisp greens. Garnish with apple wedges, if desired.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, cooking oil and apricot nectar.
Mix well.
Then add eggs and beat about 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: boy scouts eat well stew
directions: After cleaning wild game wash thoroughly in cold water.
Soak 4 to 5 hours in a solution of 1/2 cup salt, 1/4 cup baking soda and 6 quarts water, making sure meat is well covered.
You may soak another 4 to 5 hours in 1 cup vinegar to 6 quarts of water.
This takes the wild taste out.
A young deer has a stronger taste than squirrel or rabbit so when cooking use garlic, onions and/or a few potatoes.
Use your favorite seasonings on wild game.

title: green beans baked
directions: Place beans and garlic powder in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Drain.
Stir together milk and mushroom soup. Alternate layers of beans, soup and cheese.
Begin with beans and end with cheese.
Top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed cabbages
directions: Remove cabbage leaves from head and boil in salted water until soft.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Combine first 6 ingredients. Mix. Spoon meat onto each leaf.
Roll.
Put toothpick to keep together.
Put in large pan.
Add one quart of tomato juice, sugar and salt to taste.
Bake 1 hour slowly.

title: carrots amandine
directions: Peel carrots and cut in 1/2-inch slices.
In a saucepan, place water.
Add sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add carrots and cook, covered, for 10 minutes or until just tender.
Drain.
Keep carrots in a warm dish.
In a small skillet, saute almonds in butter over medium heat.
Stir and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour almond and butter mixture over carrots and mix.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in a jar. Use 2 teaspoons per 6 ounce serving. Serve hot or cold.

title: indian relish
directions: Chop vegetables. Stir in the salt.
Let sit for at least 3 hours (or longer). Drain as much of the brine off as possible. Add sugar, vinegar and spices.
Mix well.
Let boil 3 minutes. Pack 1/2-inch from top of jars.
Process in water bath 5 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, gelatin, and sugar.
Then add water and food color. Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add strawberries and pour into baked pie crust.
Refrigerate until cold.
Top with whipping cream, if desired.

title: best ever broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and combine all ingredients except crumbs and butter.
Place in buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and dot with butter. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: connie's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except nuts).
Roll in a ball or log; cover with nuts.
Chill.
Serve with choice of crackers.

title: mom's marinated chicken
directions: Marinate chicken overnight.
Roll in bread crumbs and bake in dish with melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook soup, onion, chilies and 3/4 can chicken broth, stirring often.
In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish, place a tortilla in each corner.
Top with some chicken, cheese and enough soup to moisten tortillas well.
Repeat this layer order until dish is filled. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will also need 1 punch bowl.

title: coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large bowl.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool 15 minutes in pans, remove from pans.
Frost with Coconut Cream frosting.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and vanilla. Add mixture of shortening, 1/3 cup buttermilk and mashed very ripe bananas.
Beat 2 minutes, then add 1/3 cup more buttermilk and eggs.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with traditional buttercream frosting when cool.

title: terrific trifle
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Cool by adding ice.
Tear angel food cake apart and pour jello over it.
Mix condensed milk with 1 1/2 cups water; add instant pudding.
Beat cream and fold into pudding/milk mixture.
Layer cake, peaches, bananas and cream.
Chill.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda and salt.
In saucepan, combine butter, water and cocoa, stirring constantly.
Bring to rolling boil over medium heat.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well. Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla flavoring.

title: diabetic casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion and peppers until brown.
Drain off fat. Alternate layers of beef, sliced potatoes, carrots and rice.
Pour smashed tomatoes over the top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar, lemon rind and juice, ginger and salt.
In another bowl, mix chicken, grapes, celery and almonds.
Add to mayonnaise mixture; blend.
Cover. Chill at least two hours before serving.
Serve on cantaloupe rings or lettuce. Serves 6 to 8.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Set aside.
Mix together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add to the mixture the Worcestershire sauce and dried beef.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped walnuts.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: broiled steak
directions: Place steaks in baking pan.
Almost cover with water.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Broil in oven at 375° until meat is tender.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix ingredients in crock-pot. Heat. Serve.

title: skillet zucchini dinner
directions: In 10-inch skillet, brown beef with onion and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add zucchini.
Cook covered 7 minutes or until zucchini is tender.
Top with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put yeast in lukewarm water to soften. Scald milk and add sugar, salt and shortening. Let cool to lukewarm. Add 2 cups flour and mix thoroughly. Add egg(s) and softened yeast. Beat well. Add enough more flour to make a soft dough. Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth. Place in a large greased bowl and turn once to grease all sides. Cover with Saran Wrap that has been lightly sprayed with cooking spray on 1 side. This will keep dough from sticking. Put in refrigerator overnight or at least several hours.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and let stand 2 to 3 hours. Stir often, about every 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Drain squash mixture and add to boiling mixture; boil 3 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Cook the ground beef and onion together.
Pour half in casserole dish.
Crumble chips over, then cheese slices.
Pour remaining ground beef over, then chips and cheese.
Cook milk, soups and Ro-Tel together.
Pour over ground beef mixture.
Lay cheese slices on. Crumble chips on top.
Cook at 350° until cheese boils.

title: old fashion vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar until dissolved.
Blend in condensed milk and flavoring.
Pour into freezer and fill to line with regular milk.
Freeze.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat pineapple. Add Jell-O and dissolve.
Add cherries and Coke.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a casserole and salt and pepper to
taste.
Add
the soups and Tater Tots to the meat. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli per package directions.
Mix soup, lemon juice, milk and mayonnaise together.
Spread broccoli on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in first mixture.
Spread batter in greased pan, 9-inches square.
Arrange apple slices on top of batter, pressing them in slightly.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 teaspoons sugar mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box and bake.
Cool as directed using 2 pans sprayed with Pam.
Mix each box of jello with 1/2 cup hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and mix.
With cakes still in pans, poke holes throughout with meat fork.
Pour jello over cake - slowly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Loosen cake from pans and use the Cool whip for frosting.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Add buttermilk to make a thin batter.
Pour into a 9-inch greased iron skillet. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: taco salad casserole for a crowd
directions: You will need 3 (12 x 20 x 2-inch) pans.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix and cook in unbaked pie shell at 325° until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: stroganoff with venison
directions: Combine seasoning and flour.
Toss meat; brown in oil.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Continue to brown 3 to 4 minutes.
Add butter and 3 tablespoons flour.
Mix broth and cook until thick. Add the meat mixture and sour cream.
Cook 1 package noodles until tender.
Serve meat over buttered noodles.
This is good!!!!

title: 24-hour salad in layers
directions: Shred lettuce, green onions, celery and water chestnuts. Sprinkle peas over layers.
Spread mayonnaise over layers of vegetables.
Seal.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over vegetables.
Mix sugar, seasoning salt and garlic salt.
Sprinkle over top. Sprinkle eggs and bacon chips over layers.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: frozen lime pie
directions: Mix milk and juice, add a few drops green food coloring and fold into Cool Whip.
Place in crust and freeze.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften the cream cheese and peanut butter in the microwave for 30 - 60 seconds on medium and cream together thoroughly.
Add sugar to the peanut butter mixture and mix thoroughly,
then add whipped topping and mix thoroughly.
Smooth into pie shell(s). Add chocolate or caramel syrup
or more whipped topping and chocolate shavings before refrigerating.
This makes 1 huge
pie or 2 average pies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a full boil. Boil for 1 minute; time accurately.
Add salt and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls or equal scoops on wax paper.
Cool until firm, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with flour, about four or five cups.
Roll on floured board and cut into shapes.
(Don't roll too thin or it will be crispy.)
Bake at 425° for ten to twelve minutes (don't overbake or they will be crispy).

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, add onion.
Add beaten egg and milk; stirring lightly.
Drop 1 teaspoon of batter for each hush puppy into hot grease.
Fry a few at a time until golden brown.

title: lenten turkish dish
directions: Slice eggplant, zucchini and potatoes in 1-inch thick slices. Dredge in flour and fry in hot oil.
Remove from heat and place in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice
directions: Mix in crock-pot the three cans of soup and rice.
Place the chicken breasts on top of this mixture, then add the celery and onion.
Cook for 3 hours on high or 4 hours on low.
Makes 4 servings.
May add 1/2 cup more rice and 2 more chicken breasts to serve 6.

title: zucchini tomato bake
directions: Combine zucchini and seasonings in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover.
Place in microwave oven and cook 10 minutes, stirring once after 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce on top and continue cooking 3 to 5 minutes.

title: apple latkes(pancakes)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Drop by tablespoon into deep hot fat and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: crescent bacon brunch
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a small mixing bowl, combine bacon, eggs, milk and onion; set aside.
Separate crescent roll dough and place in the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1 inch up the side of the pan to form a crust.
Place cheese over the crust.
Pour egg mixture over the cheese.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes, until lightly brown and a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
For easier handling, cool 5 to 10 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: holy smoke
directions: Mix oleo and flour.
Pat into pan.
Pat 1/2 cup nuts into this.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes, until brown.
Cool.
Cream together confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread on crust.
Mix pudding and milk (thick). Spread over cream cheese layer.
Put rest of whipped topping on next and put nuts on top.

title: white chocolate bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut bread into 3/4-inch squares; place in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly-roll pan and bake 15 minutes or until toasted, stirring once.
Grease shallow 3 3/4-quart casserole.
In 4-quart saucepan, heat cream, milk and sugar to boiling over medium-high heat.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate.

title: sweet and sour chicken(6 servings)
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Add water to juice to equal 2 1/4 cups total (this is to cook rice in).
Saute onion in shortening until tender.
Add chicken stock or water and chicken bouillon cubes and carrots.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and ginger; add catsup, vinegar and soy sauce. Stir into vegetable mixture and coat until clear and thickened. Add chicken, green pepper and pineapple.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Bring pineapple juice/water mixture to boil with salt and pepper. Stir in rice.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Serve chicken mixture over rice.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese and onion.
Spread on slice of dried beef.
Roll up and chill.

title: jerry's braunschweiger pate
directions: Mash braunschweiger and combine with dip mix, sugar and water. Blend thoroughly.
Form into
an Igloo shape, place on serving plate.
Chill.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate egg yolks from whites and set aside.
Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in a large saucepan.
Add water and cook on medium heat until smooth.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken; then add butter and vanilla. Stir in real good.
When thick, pour in cooled pie shells.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix jello in cold water.
Add boiling water.
Stir in sugar and strawberries.
Mix 2 packages of Dream Whip; fold into jello mixture.
Cut cake in small pieces.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together strawberries, bananas, strawberry glaze and 7-up. Pinch angel food cake into small pieces.
Stir cake into fruit mixture and top with cool whip.
Garnish with strawberry slices. Chill and serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss together the chicken, celery, parsley, salt and pepper. Fold in carefully the whipped cream, mayo, lemon juice and toasted almonds. Serve on little sandwiches.
